(73, 'GK', 'English', 'Abinash Bhattacharjee: Ghadar Patriot and Cellular Jail Freedom Fighter', '1', '3', '39', 'ddb7283023cc791ce80cb0e8ccc10815.jpg', '', '1757059501_Abinash Chandra Bhattacharjee.pdf', 'Abinash Chandra Bhattacharjee was a revolutionary associated with India’s early armed struggle for independence. Closely linked to the Jugantar Party and the Ghadar Movement, he was arrested for seditious activities and sentenced to Kala Pani at the Cellular Jail. He symbolizes the sacrifices made by young revolutionaries during the colonial era who fought British oppression through radical means.', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(74, 'GK', 'English', 'Ullaskar Dutta: Revolutionary Bomb Maker Deported to Cellular Jail, Kalapani', '', '', '', 'fdc645dcc65a9a071d66c06708f64be5.jpg', '', '1757063597_Ullaskar Dutta.pdf', 'Ullaskar Dutta was a prominent revolutionary associated with the Anushilan Samiti. Arrested in 1908 in the Alipore Bomb Case, he was sentenced to life and deported to the Cellular Jail in the Andamans. His incarceration saw extreme torture, leading to a mental breakdown. He was later released in 1915 and became a vocal critic of British colonial repression.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(75, 'GK', 'English', 'Indu Bhushan Roy: Forgotten Revolutionary Martyr of Cellular Jail History', '', '', '', '402d1aa53aaa434c4de03d63b46cedf4.jpg', '', '1757064614_Indu Bhushan Roy.pdf', 'Indu Bhushan Roy was a valiant Bengali revolutionary linked with the Anushilan Samiti. Arrested for his involvement in armed resistance, he was deported to the infamous Cellular Jail in the Andamans. Tortured severely, he died under suspicious circumstances—likely suicide or custodial killing—becoming one of the earliest martyrs of Kalapani, symbolizing the brutality faced by political prisoners.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(76, 'GK', 'English', 'Trailokyanath Chakraborty: Voice Against Colonial Rule and Injustice', '', '', '', 'b64688ee3f448233b303345726f5233f.jpg', '', '1757064936_Trailokyanath Chakraborty.pdf', 'Trailokyanath Chakraborty was a prominent Bengali revolutionary and freedom fighter associated with the Anushilan Samiti. Arrested multiple times by the British, he was deported to the Cellular Jail in the Andamans. Even after release, he remained active in the nationalist struggle. His life symbolized relentless resistance, ideological clarity, and sacrifice in the fight for India\'s independence.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(77, 'GK', 'English', 'Vinayak Damodar (Veer) Savarkar: Hindutva theorist, revolutionary, writer, and Cellular Jail prisoner', '', '', '', '55c34eeb912e92cd21fecfd2accaa871.jpeg', '', '1757065529_Vinayak Damodar (Veer) Savarkar.pdf', 'Vinayak Damodar Savarkar (1883–1966) was a revolutionary, poet, and political ideologue who pioneered the concept of Hindutva. He founded Abhinav Bharat Society and influenced the armed struggle for India’s independence. Imprisoned in the Andamans, later led Hindu Mahasabha. Though controversial, he inspired generations with his writings and fearless resistance to colonial rule.', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(78, 'GK', 'English', 'Bhai Parmanand: Arya Samaj missionary turned Ghadar revolutionary and Hindu Mahasabha leader', '', '', '', 'd807de3df93081d81a481a904ace16ba.jpg', '', '1757066018_Bhai Parmanand.pdf', 'Bhai Parmanand (4 November 1876 – 8 December 1947) was a Mohyal Brahmin Arya Samajist from Punjab who travelled abroad as a missionary and connected with Lala Hardayal. A founding member of the Ghadar Party, he co-led the 1915 Lahore Conspiracy. Sentenced to death, later commuted to life, spent years in Andamans, launched a prolonged hunger strike, and later led Hindu Mahasabha.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(79, 'GK', 'English', 'Shambhu Nath Azad: Chambal-born revolutionary, hunger striker, daring bank raid leader', '', '', '', '8f15513885e66033d803ad5e48eb4bd2.jpg', '', '1757066603_Shambhu Nath Azad.pdf', 'Shambhu Nath Azad, born in Agra (Kachhaura Ghat, Chambal region), joined Naujawan Bharat Sabha and Anushilan Samiti in his teens. Trained in guerrilla tactics, he formed a clandestine group (“Dasta”) in 1932 after release from jail. He orchestrated the daring Udhagamandalam (Ooty) bank robbery in April 1933 and endured long jail terms in Cellular Jail, including hunger strikes.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(80, 'GK', 'English', 'Upendra Nath Banerjee: Revolutionary Transported to Andamans for Sedition', '1', '3', '39', '2f45d6f666f0ab2b713f5e6b717cc8ca.jpg', '', '1757067929_Upendra Nath Banerjee.pdf', 'Upendra Nath Banerjee was a courageous revolutionary associated with the Anushilan Samiti. Arrested for his role in anti-British conspiracies, he was sentenced to Kala Pani—transportation for life to the Cellular Jail in the Andaman Islands. He represents a generation of patriots who dared to defy British colonialism through radical activism and underground movements.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(81, 'GK', 'English', 'Barindra Ghosh: Revolutionary Journalist and Alipore Bomb Case Accused', '1', '3', '39', '422135244a3242ff423aec17db4b8151.jpg', '', '1757068265_Barindra Kumar Ghosh.pdf', 'Barindra Kumar Ghosh was a key figure in India’s revolutionary nationalist movement and the younger brother of philosopher Sri Aurobindo. He founded the revolutionary journal Jugantar and was implicated in the Alipore Bomb Case. Initially sentenced to death, his punishment was commuted to life imprisonment in the Andaman’s Cellular Jail, marking his place in history among the notable Kala Pani convicts.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(82, 'GK', 'English', 'Mohit Moitra: Martyr of Cellular Jail’s Historic 1933 Hunger Strike', '1', '3', '39', '70dfddee4571ae1fcdaf5f556579d4b4.jpg', '', '1757068791_Mohit Moitra.pdf', 'Mohit Moitra was a Bengali revolutionary and a member of the Jugantar group. Arrested for his anti-British activities, he was deported to the Cellular Jail. In 1933, he joined a hunger strike to protest the inhumane treatment of political prisoners. He died after being forcibly fed by jail authorities, becoming one of the three martyrs of that strike.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(83, 'GK', 'English', 'Mohan Kishore Namadas: Revolutionary Martyr of Cellular Jail Hunger Strike', '1', '3', '39', 'ae2dfbb25e06bafb627e0a3fed83e921.jpg', '', '1757069671_Mohan Kishore Namadas.pdf', 'Mohan Kishore Namadas, a Bengali revolutionary, was a key member of the Anushilan Samiti. Arrested for revolutionary activities, he was sentenced to life imprisonment and deported to the Cellular Jail. In 1933, during a hunger strike for better treatment of political prisoners, he died due to brutal forced feeding. His martyrdom highlighted British cruelty in penal colonies.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(84, 'GK', 'English', 'Mahavir Singh: Martyr Who Defied British Rule in Cellular Jail', '1', '3', '39', '6d5a8fe51ebaf2164a78891b0e9d06cb.jpg', '', '1757071092_Mahavir Singh.pdf', 'Mahavir Singh, a courageous revolutionary from Uttar Pradesh, joined the Hindustan Socialist Republican Association (HSRA). He was imprisoned and sent to the Cellular Jail in the Andamans. While protesting against the brutal treatment of fellow prisoners, he undertook a hunger strike. He died during forced feeding, becoming one of the first martyrs of Cellular Jail.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(85, 'GK', 'English', ' Khudiram Bose: Young Revolutionary, Symbol of Courage and Sacrifice', '1', '3', '39', '7344218a1ddddb2d945fd211ec5f1ae3.jpg', '', '1757071333_Khudiram Bosh.pdf', 'Khudiram Bose was one of India’s youngest freedom fighters, martyred at just 18. Born in Midnapore in 1889, he joined the revolutionary Anushilan Samiti. In the Muzaffarpur Conspiracy Case, he attempted to assassinate a British judge but mistakenly killed two women. Captured and hanged in 1908, he remains a symbol of courage, with his legacy honored across India.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(86, 'GK', 'English', 'Bhagat Singh: Revolutionary Icon Who Challenged British Rule with Courage', '1', '3', '39', '788ef6588d28d28962e494f858e953ae.jpg', '', '1757072129_Bhagat Singh.pdf', 'Bhagat Singh was a socialist revolutionary who opposed British colonialism through radical means. Influenced by Marxism and nationalism, he participated in significant acts like the Assembly bombing and Saunders\' assassination. Hanged at 23, he became a martyr. His legacy inspires youth, symbolizing bravery, ideology-driven action, and ultimate sacrifice for India’s freedom.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(87, 'GK', 'English', 'Shivaram Rajguru: Brave Revolutionary and Martyr of India’s Freedom Struggle', '1', '3', '39', 'd5b68ffd2c68b4efafabe099a7172cf2.jpg', '', '1757072632_Shivaram Rajguru.pdf', 'Shivaram Rajguru was a fearless revolutionary from Maharashtra who fought against British rule. As a member of HSRA, he participated in the assassination of British officer John Saunders alongside Bhagat Singh and Sukhdev. A firm believer in armed resistance, Rajguru was hanged on 23 March 1931. He is remembered as a symbol of youthful sacrifice and patriotism.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(88, 'GK', 'English', 'Sukhdev Thapar: Committed Revolutionary and Martyr of India’s Freedom Struggle', '1', '3', '39', '0433c45fdd396b4371b821c486b16e6d.jpg', '', '1757072988_Sukhdev Thapar.pdf', 'Sukhdev Thapar was a dedicated revolutionary from Punjab who played a key role in India’s freedom struggle. As a senior member of HSRA, he helped organize revolutionary cells and participated in the Saunders assassination. Known for his discipline and leadership, he was executed with Bhagat Singh and Rajguru on 23 March 1931. His martyrdom remains an inspiration.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(89, 'GK', 'English', 'Ram Prasad Bismil: Poet Revolutionary Behind Kakori Conspiracy Against British Rule', '1', '3', '39', 'f1a81f2838d15bf27ab7fcfaffad95d2.jpg', '', '1757073299_Ram Prasad Bismil.pdf', 'Ram Prasad Bismil was a prominent revolutionary, poet, and freedom fighter who fought British colonialism through armed struggle. He co-founded the Hindustan Republican Association (HRA) and led the famous Kakori Train Robbery of 1925. A powerful orator and nationalist poet, Bismil was executed in 1927, leaving behind a legacy of patriotism and poetic resistance.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(90, 'GK', 'English', 'Ashfaqulla Khan: Martyr Who Fought British Rule With Brotherhood', '1', '3', '39', 'a29c7b82effec14da37d2e93593aaf8e.jpg', '', '1757073643_Ashfaqulla Khan.pdf', 'Ashfaqulla Khan was a freedom fighter and poet who fought British colonialism through revolutionary means. As a key member of the Hindustan Republican Association, he took part in the Kakori Train Robbery. Committed to Hindu-Muslim unity and patriotic ideals, he was executed in 1927. His martyrdom stands as a symbol of secular nationalism and youthful sacrifice.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(91, 'GK', 'English', 'Thakur Roshan Singh: Forgotten Martyr of the Kakori Conspiracy Case', '1', '3', '39', 'b2ab35ab250a47fd14a94d9ef3981376.jpg', '', '1757073855_Thakur Roshan Singh.pdf', 'Thakur Roshan Singh was a revolutionary associated with the Hindustan Republican Association. Though not directly involved in the Kakori train robbery, he was arrested for earlier revolutionary actions and executed for conspiracy. He was hanged on 19 December 1927, alongside Ashfaqulla Khan and Ram Prasad Bismil, marking him as one of the silent martyrs of India’s freedom movement.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(92, 'GK', 'English', 'Rajendra Lahiri: Brave Revolutionary Hanged Before Kakori Martyrs in 1927', '1', '3', '39', '27eb684831b2eace1793cafe4526ee62.jpg', '', '1757074241_Rajendra Lahiri.pdf', 'Rajendra Lahiri was a freedom fighter associated with the Hindustan Republican Association (HRA). He was involved in the 1925 Kakori Conspiracy aimed at robbing a British treasury train. Convicted along with others, he was hanged on 17 December 1927 in Gonda Jail—two days before Bismil, Ashfaqulla, and Roshan Singh. His early execution sparked outrage and became a symbol of colonial injustice.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(93, 'GK', 'English', 'Prafulla Chaki: Young Revolutionary Who Chose Death Over British Arrest', '1', '3', '39', '1a27a01a46a4484b6e356bb320dfb86a.jpg', '', '1757074594_Prafulla Chaki.pdf', 'Prafulla Chaki was a Bengali revolutionary who attempted to assassinate a British judge during the Muzaffarpur Conspiracy of 1908. Partnering with Khudiram Bose, he threw a bomb at a carriage but mistakenly killed civilians. While escaping, he was cornered at Mokama Ghat and shot himself to avoid arrest. His martyrdom inspired generations of revolutionaries during India’s freedom movement.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(94, 'GK', 'English', 'Mangal Pandey Ignited 1857 Revolt, Defied British Colonial Oppression Boldly', '1', '3', '39', '26343e02ac546ffd4d9eccdb13300c8b.jpg', '', '1757075121_Mangal Pandey.pdf', 'Mangal Pandey, a sepoy in the 34th Bengal Native Infantry, ignited India’s First War of Independence in 1857 by revolting against the use of greased rifle cartridges that insulted Hindu and Muslim religious sentiments. His act of rebellion at Barrackpore led to his execution but became the symbolic starting point of India\'s armed struggle against British colonial rule.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(95, 'GK', 'English', 'sdcwnsdcn ', NULL, NULL, '1', '16a1bb5ce98eeba49f8152c14999fd79.png', 'https://example.com/images/history.jpg', '1757171713_Advance_Topic.pdf', 'wsdvesvc', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(96, 'GK', 'English', 'Udham Singh Avenged Jallianwala Bagh Massacre, Martyred in London', '1', '3', '39', '6e91ca4aeeec6f9a885bfe8885e514b6.jpg', '', '1757323013_Udham Singh.pdf', 'Udham Singh, a revolutionary from Punjab, assassinated General Michael O\'Dwyer in 1940 to avenge the 1919 Jallianwala Bagh massacre. A member of the Ghadar Party and later influenced by socialism, Singh waited over two decades for justice. Captured and tried in Britain, he was hanged in London. His sacrifice is remembered as a symbol of anti-colonial vengeance and resistance.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(97, 'GK', 'English', 'Teen Revolutionary Anant Kanhere Hanged for Killing British Collector Jackson', '1', '3', '39', '532922707e0ef6135c1f61eb069b026c.jpg', 'https://example.com/images/history.jpg', '1757323586_Anant Laxman Kanher.pdf', 'Anant Laxman Kanher, a young revolutionary from Maharashtra, assassinated British Collector A.M.T. Jackson in 1909 to protest colonial oppression. Influenced by nationalist ideals, he carried out the act at a public event in Nashik. Arrested on the spot, he was tried and hanged at age 18 in 1910. His execution remains a symbol of youthful sacrifice in India’s freedom movement.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(98, 'GK', 'English', 'Teen Freedom Fighter Hemu Kalani Hanged by British at Nineteen', '1', '3', '39', 'e2a1e35472cb0c7621545c2533bd960f.jpg', '', '1757323736_Hemu Kalani.pdf', 'Hemu Kalani was a teenage revolutionary from Sindh who led anti-British protests during the Quit India Movement. He attempted to derail a British military train carrying troops and arms. Caught and tortured, Hemu refused to betray his comrades. He was hanged on January 21, 1943, becoming one of the youngest martyrs of India’s struggle for independence.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(99, 'GK', 'English', 'Satyendranath Bosu Hanged For Role In Chittagong Armoury Raid', '1', '3', '39', '503e30b9542bd1b84eef19f9f5606835.jpg', '', '1757324132_Satyendranath Bosu .pdf', 'Satyendranath Bosu was a Bengali revolutionary associated with the Chittagong Armoury Raid of 1930 led by Surya Sen. Deeply inspired by nationalist ideas, he played a key role in the armed insurrection against British rule. Captured after the raid, he was sentenced to death and hanged in July 1934, becoming one of the unsung heroes of India’s independence movement.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(100, 'GK', 'English', 'Ramkrishna Biswas Hanged for Attempted Assassination of British Officer', '1', '3', '39', 'c43344f70928ccd15603430f1f37fa86.jpg', '', '1757324701_Ramkrishna Biswas .pdf', 'Ramkrishna Biswas was a revolutionary from Bengal associated with the Jugantar group. In 1930, he attempted to assassinate a British magistrate as an act of anti-colonial resistance but mistakenly killed another officer. He was arrested, tried, and hanged in 1931. His execution inspired numerous revolutionaries, including Subhas Chandra Bose, and remains a symbol of youthful sacrifice.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(101, 'GK', 'English', 'Ghulam Husain Martyred For Role In Chittagong Armoury Raid, 1934', '1', '3', '39', '94a696c0c056c066d6b6b29f03f5724c.jpg', '', '1757325085_Ghulam Husain .pdf', 'Ghulam Husain, a brave revolutionary from Bengal, participated in the Chittagong Armoury Raid of 1930, orchestrated by Surya Sen. His mission was to liberate India through armed rebellion. Arrested during the British crackdown, he was sentenced to death and hanged in July 1934. Though less known, he remains an important figure in India\'s armed freedom struggle.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(102, 'GK', 'English', 'Basanta Kumar Biswas: Young Revolutionary Hanged for Delhi Bomb Attack', '1', '3', '39', 'f28eb9a77995657b79378d1e2d2fcdaa.jpg', '', '1757325978_Basanta Kumar Biswas.pdf', 'Basanta Kumar Biswas, a young Bengali revolutionary, played a key role in the 1912 Delhi Conspiracy. At just 18, he was involved in an assassination attempt on Viceroy Lord Hardinge during a state procession. Arrested and tried under the British regime, he was hanged on 11 May 1915. His sacrifice remains a powerful symbol of youthful patriotism.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(103, 'GK', 'English', 'Bhai Balmukund: Delhi Conspiracy Martyr Executed in British India', '1', '3', '39', '12a2d9019baf49f29d2ea5285ecd6b93.jpg', '', '1757326643_Bhai Balmukund.pdf', 'Bhai Balmukund was a revolutionary deeply involved in the 1912 Delhi Conspiracy, which targeted Viceroy Lord Hardinge. A cousin of revolutionary Bhai Parmanand, Balmukund was arrested in 1914, tried under charges of conspiracy and sedition, and hanged at the Lahore Central Jail in May 1915. He remains remembered as a brave nationalist who sacrificed his life at just 26.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(104, 'GK', 'English', 'Tatya Tope Led Fierce Guerrilla Campaigns During 1857 Revolt Heroically', '1', '3', '39', 'fc00efc148feda71e54ddfb9e3aacd6d.jpg', '', '1757320745_Tatya Tope.pdf', 'Tatya Tope, a key leader in the 1857 Revolt, was a trusted general of Nana Sahib. Known for his strategic brilliance and guerrilla warfare, he led forces in Kanpur, Gwalior, and central India. Even after losing territory, he continued resistance until captured and executed in 1859. Tatya remains one of India’s earliest revolutionary icons for his unmatched military defiance.', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(105, 'GK', 'English', 'Vanchinathan Assassinated British Collector, Sparked Early Nationalist Resistance', '1', '3', '39', 'f4636d46aa34840f203aef4ab59d4c1c.jpg', '', '1757321161_Vanchinathan Iyer.pdf', 'Vanchinathan was a Tamil revolutionary who assassinated British Collector Robert Ashe in 1911 at Maniyachi railway station. Motivated by the Swadeshi movement and colonial atrocities, he viewed Ashe as an oppressor. After the act, Vanchinathan died by suicide to avoid capture. Though controversial, he remains a symbol of early militant resistance in India’s freedom struggle, especially in South India.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(106, 'GK', 'English', 'Dinesh Gupta Fought Colonial Rule, Embraced Martyrdom With Courage', '1', '3', '39', '55a54b3b9621cb2f74952b38edc437b2.jpg', '', '1757321583_Dinesh Gupta.pdf', 'Dinesh Gupta, a young Bengali revolutionary, was a key figure in India’s anti-colonial movement. In 1931, he and his comrades attacked the Writers’ Building in Kolkata to assassinate British officials. Though the mission partly failed, Gupta was captured and executed at just 19. His bravery and sacrifice remain etched in the history of Bengal’s revolutionary struggle against British rule.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(107, 'GK', 'English', 'Kartar Singh Sarabha Inspired Ghadar Movement, Martyred at Age Nineteen', '1', '3', '39', '69082f39abe02ae66e8fde17be2231ab.jpg', '', '1757322239_Kartar Singh Sarabha.pdf', 'Kartar Singh Sarabha was a fiery revolutionary and one of the youngest martyrs of India’s freedom struggle. A leader of the Ghadar Movement, he sought to incite mutiny in the British Indian Army during World War I. Caught by the British, he was tried and hanged at the age of 19. His sacrifice deeply inspired revolutionaries like Bhagat Singh.', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(108, 'GK', 'English', 'Pandit Kanshi Ram: Ghadar Revolutionary Martyred for India’s Freedom Struggle', '1', '3', '39', 'fa260a13552ab5757cc6cbf54d388f2d.jpg', '', '1757327281_Pandit Kanshi Ram.pdf', 'Pandit Kanshi Ram was a key leader in the Ghadar Movement, which aimed to incite armed revolt against British rule in India. A close associate of Lala Hardayal and Vishnu Ganesh Pingle, he was arrested for attempting mutiny in the British Indian Army. He was tried under the Lahore Conspiracy Case and hanged in Lahore on 27 March 1915.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(109, 'GK', 'English', 'Babarao Savarkar: Revolutionary Who Faced Kala Pani Punishment Bravely', '1', '3', '39', '9e21d0144e3631ba58175ea10afcc638.jpg', '', '1757328080_Babarao Savarkar.pdf', 'Babarao Savarkar, elder brother of Veer Savarkar, was a fearless revolutionary and co-founder of the Abhinav Bharat Society. Convicted for sedition, he was sentenced to Kala Pani at Cellular Jail, Andaman. Despite harsh conditions, he remained committed to India’s independence. A forgotten patriot, his life embodies the unsung sacrifices made in India’s freedom movement.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(110, 'GK', 'English', 'Batukeshwar Dutt: Revolutionary Who Defied British Rule With Bombs', '1', '3', '39', '1bcfbc6c8276f08a7f72b21adde00a90.jpg', '', '1757328235_Batukeshwar Dutt.pdf', 'Batukeshwar Dutt was a fearless revolutionary who, alongside Bhagat Singh, threw bombs in the Central Legislative Assembly in 1929 to protest British tyranny. He was sentenced to life imprisonment and sent to the Cellular Jail (Kala Pani). Despite harsh treatment, he remained committed to the freedom struggle. His legacy continues as an icon of fearless protest and sacrifice.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(111, 'GK', 'English', 'Yogendra Shukla: Revolutionary Leader and Architect of Bihar’s Resistance', '1', '3', '39', '321f39d84ce8cdd318587782d4d2304f.jpg', '', '1757328333_Yogendra Shukla.pdf', 'Yogendra Shukla was a prominent revolutionary from Bihar and a founding member of the Hindustan Socialist Republican Association (HSRA). He played a key role in organizing resistance against British rule. Sentenced to life imprisonment, he was deported to the Cellular Jail. Despite prolonged incarceration, his contributions continued post-release through the Quit India Movement and as a mentor to young revolutionaries.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(112, 'GK', 'English', 'From Empire to Republic: Historical Journey of India’s Constitution', '5', '28', '46', '0d7946bd78fd795b8f1c59c6f0c9039e.jpg', '', '1757330144_From Empire to Republic_ Historical Journey of India’s Constitution.pdf', 'The Indian Constitution’s origins span over two centuries, from British colonial laws to nationalist movements demanding self-rule. Key milestones include the Government of India Acts, the Nehru Report, Round Table Conferences, and the 1935 Act. The 1946–1949 Constituent Assembly debates, guided by B.R. Ambedkar and others, shaped a sovereign, democratic, and inclusive Constitution, adopted on 26 November 1949.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(113, 'GK', 'English', 'Constituent Assembly: Crafting India’s Constitution Through Committees and Consensus', '5', '28', '46', 'c75f0b0f9b35a211e7c8c44d6c379e71.jpeg', '', '1757330327_Constituent Assembly_ Crafting India’s Constitution Through Committees and Consensus.pdf', 'The Constituent Assembly of India (1946–1950) framed the Constitution through structured debates, expert committees, and meticulous drafting. Comprising 389 members initially, it worked in 11 sessions over 165 days. Led by figures like Dr. B.R. Ambedkar, Jawaharlal Nehru, and Sardar Patel, the Assembly processed thousands of amendments, producing a democratic, federal, and rights-based governance framework.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(114, 'GK', 'English', 'Global Inspirations Behind India’s Unique and Comprehensive Constitution', '5', '28', '46', 'f66869a66ed4e811d0b8d460e1ce36fd.jpg', '', '1757330668_Global Inspirations Behind India’s Unique and Comprehensive Constitution.pdf', 'The Indian Constitution, adopted in 1950, is a synthesis of global ideals and governance models tailored to India’s needs. Drawing from sources like the Government of India Act 1935, and constitutions of the USA, UK, Canada, Ireland, Australia, France, and others, it blends democracy, federalism, justice, and rights into a robust framework for the world’s largest democracy.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(115, 'GK', 'English', 'Adoption and Salient Features of the Indian Constitution Explained', '5', '28', '46', 'd9f0ee093f6d334034309748c2b311e0.jpeg', '', '1757330929_Adoption and Salient Features of the Indian Constitution Explained.pdf', 'The Constitution of India, adopted on 26 November 1949, partially enforced certain provisions immediately and fully commenced on 26 January 1950, now celebrated as Republic Day. As the world’s lengthiest written constitution, it blends federal and unitary elements, guarantees rights, outlines duties, and establishes parliamentary democracy, embodying principles drawn from global sources adapted to India’s unique diversity.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(116, 'GK', 'English', 'Preamble of India: Foundation of Sovereignty, Justice, Liberty, Equality, Fraternity', '5', '28', '47', '9f07262f9857f79065c335036cff01ee.png', '', '1757331885_Published - Preamble of India_ Foundation of Sovereignty, Justice, Liberty, Equality, Fraternity.pdf', 'The Preamble of the Indian Constitution outlines the nation’s core values—sovereignty, socialism, secularism, democracy, and republicanism. It declares justice, liberty, equality, and fraternity as guiding principles. Added through the 42nd Amendment, key terms shape governance and law. While not enforceable, courts use it for interpretation, making it a vital statement of India’s constitutional philosophy.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(117, 'GK', 'English', 'India’s Preamble: History, Amendment, and Supreme Court Interpretations Explained', '5', '28', '47', 'fd3d056fe2b2aa148124976c6b4fe918.jpg', '', '1757331798_India’s Preamble_ History, Amendment, and Supreme Court Interpretations Explained.pdf', 'The Preamble to India’s Constitution has been amended only once, through the 42nd Amendment in 1976, adding “Socialist,” “Secular,” and “Integrity.” Landmark Supreme Court rulings have clarified its status as part of the Constitution and protected its core values under the basic structure doctrine. Recent debates seek removal of added terms, but courts uphold their inclusion.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(118, 'GK', 'English', 'Supreme Court Affirms Preamble’s Role in India’s Constitutional Framework', '5', '28', '47', 'fa51319c064cf38d7dd530f1a31fb9d0.jpeg', '', '1757332534_Supreme Court Affirms Preamble’s Role in India’s Constitutional Framework.pdf', 'The Supreme Court of India has evolved its stance on the Preamble—from Berubari’s non-operative view to Kesavananda Bharati’s recognition of it as part of the Constitution. While amendable, it remains a guide to interpretation and a marker of the basic structure. Key rulings uphold values like secularism, socialism, democracy, and balance between rights and directives.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(119, 'GK', 'English', 'Fundamental Rights in India: Scope, Classification, and Constitutional Safeguards', '5', '28', '48', 'fc05774286c3ff7dc617e24eacb01fe2.jpg', '', '1757332939_Fundamental Rights in India_ Scope, Classification, and Constitutional Safeguards.pdf', 'The Indian Constitution’s Part III (Articles 12–35) enshrines Fundamental Rights, ensuring equality, liberty, and justice. Divided into six categories, these rights protect citizens against state excesses and preserve democratic values. They are enforceable through courts, subject to reasonable restrictions, and include special safeguards for vulnerable groups. Landmark amendments and judgments have shaped their scope and limitations over time.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(120, 'GK', 'English', 'Safeguarding Rights: Writs, Restrictions, and Constitutional Remedies in India', '5', '28', '48', '274ffa0fa90cd4a563b0a13efa9ba121.png', '', '1757333827_Safeguarding Rights_ Writs, Restrictions, and Constitutional Remedies in India.pdf', 'Fundamental rights in India are safeguarded through writs issued under Articles 32 and 226. These constitutional remedies—Habeas Corpus, Mandamus, Prohibition, Certiorari, and Quo Warranto—protect citizens from unlawful actions. However, rights are subject to reasonable restrictions for sovereignty, security, and public order. Landmark cases shape the balance between liberty and state control, ensuring democratic governance and judicial accountability.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(121, 'GK', 'English', 'Fundamental Duties: Citizens’ Responsibilities Shaping India’s Constitutional Democracy', '5', '28', '48', '69bbe00207f2cfc124c140644d63f08f.jpg', '', '1757334317_Fundamental Duties_ Citizens’ Responsibilities Shaping India’s Constitutional Democracy.pdf', 'Article 51A of the Indian Constitution outlines 11 Fundamental Duties, introduced by the 42nd Amendment (1976) and expanded by the 86th Amendment (2002). Though non-justiciable, they guide legislation, judicial interpretation, and civic conduct. Rooted in India’s traditions, these duties balance rights with responsibilities, inspiring harmony, environmental care, and national integrity while supporting democratic governance.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(122, 'GK', 'English', 'Directive Principles of State Policy: Vision for India’s Welfare State', '5', '28', '49', '423316303f5890768fdc92c02816d997.jpeg', '', '1757407584_Directive Principles of State Policy_ Vision for India’s Welfare State.pdf', 'The Directive Principles of State Policy (Part IV, Articles 36–51) guide India’s governance towards social, economic, and political justice. Though non-justiciable, they shape laws and policies. Classified as Socialistic, Gandhian, and Liberal-Intellectual, these principles promote welfare, decentralization, equality, environmental protection, and global peace, embodying the Constitution’s commitment to building a just, equitable, and progressive society.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(123, 'GK', 'English', 'Balancing Rights and Duties: DPSP–Fundamental Rights Constitutional Relationship', '5', '28', '49', 'c40c84376185be1bf02d02e37d602a8f.jpg', '', '1757407735_Balancing Rights and Duties_ DPSP–Fundamental Rights Constitutional Relationship.pdf', 'The Directive Principles of State Policy (DPSP) and Fundamental Rights (FRs) form the moral and legal backbone of India’s Constitution. While FRs ensure enforceable individual freedoms, DPSPs guide the State toward socio-economic justice. Courts have evolved from prioritising FRs to harmonising both, recognising their combined role as the Constitution’s conscience, ensuring liberty and social welfare coexist.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(124, 'GK', 'English', 'Directive Principles: Amendments, Implementation, and Judicial Shaping of India’s Welfare State', '5', '28', '49', 'b0abcbd9fc12165c8850a3c2495eb5cd.jpeg', '', '1757407910_Directive Principles_ Amendments, Implementation, and Judicial Shaping of India’s Welfare State.pdf', 'The Directive Principles of State Policy, enshrined in Part IV of India’s Constitution, guide governance toward a just welfare state. Though non-justiciable, they’ve been advanced through constitutional amendments, landmark court rulings, and targeted policies. From land reforms to education rights, these principles bridge aspirations and law, continually balancing with Fundamental Rights in shaping India’s socio-economic landscape.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(125, 'GK', 'English', 'India’s Constitutional Amendment: Process, Limits, and Recent Developments', '5', '28', '57', 'ca7af058b267a16e543a9b2b6251de41.jpg', '', '1757409941_India’s Constitutional Amendment_ Process, Limits, and Recent Developments.pdf', 'The Indian Constitution can be amended through procedures under Article 368, involving special majorities, and in some cases, state ratification. Amendments ensure adaptability while preserving the Constitution’s core principles. Judicial rulings, especially the Basic Structure doctrine, limit Parliament’s power. Since 1950, 106 amendments have been enacted, including the 2023 women’s reservation law, with new proposals under consideration.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(126, 'GK', 'English', 'Three Constitutional Amendment Procedures Defining India’s Governance and Federal Balance', '5', '28', '57', '1248e4199da874432c165d4497e1cfc3.jpg', '', '1757410140_Three Constitutional Amendment Procedures Defining India’s Governance and Federal Balance.pdf', 'The Indian Constitution allows amendments through three procedures—by simple majority, special majority, and special majority with state ratification—balancing flexibility and rigidity. While minor provisions need only simple majority, core rights and structures require special majorities. Federal provisions demand both Parliament’s approval and state consent, safeguarded by the Supreme Court’s basic structure doctrine to preserve constitutional integrity.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(127, 'GK', 'English', 'Key Constitutional Amendments That Shaped India’s Democracy and Governance Framework', '5', '28', '57', 'a2e219044fd0bbc119423c381ba0fea4.jpg', '', '1757410284_Key Constitutional Amendments That Shaped India’s Democracy and Governance Framework.pdf', 'India’s Constitution, a dynamic framework for governance, has evolved through crucial amendments addressing democracy, justice, equality, and federal balance. Landmark changes include the 1st Amendment’s speech limits, 42nd’s Emergency-era overhaul, 73rd’s local governance, 101st’s GST reform, and 106th’s women’s reservation. Guided by judicial review and the Basic Structure doctrine, these amendments preserve constitutional morality and adaptability.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(128, 'GK', 'English', 'Kesavananda Bharati Case: Birth and Evolution of Basic Structure Doctrine', '5', '28', '58', 'c6d5e96bf0c1f4822f0d9a57be9f8d32.jpg', '', '1757410540_Kesavananda Bharati Case_ Birth and Evolution of Basic Structure Doctrine.pdf', 'The 1973 Kesavananda Bharati judgment transformed India’s constitutional landscape, introducing the Basic Structure Doctrine. It held that Parliament’s amending power under Article 368 is wide but cannot alter the Constitution’s core identity. Evolving through landmark cases, this doctrine safeguards principles like judicial review, secularism, and federalism, ensuring democratic balance between legislative power and constitutional integrity.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(129, 'GK', 'English', 'Indian Basic Structure Doctrine: Safeguarding Core Constitutional Principles from Amendments', '5', '28', '58', 'acf3535aca0a0c121d7ac3cbd1bacdd0.jpeg', '', '1757411044_Indian Basic Structure Doctrine_ Safeguarding Core Constitutional Principles from Amendments.pdf', 'The Basic Structure Doctrine, evolved in Kesavananda Bharati (1973), limits Parliament’s amending power under Article 368 by protecting essential constitutional features like judicial review, federalism, and democracy. Through landmark cases, the Supreme Court has preserved these principles against political overreach. Recent rulings, including on electoral bonds and judicial independence, underscore its continuing role in India’s constitutional democracy.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(130, 'GK', 'English', 'Union Executive of India: Structure, Powers, Roles, and Functions', '5', '28', '59', '265302ace40007404cd4144684367e65.jpg', '', '1757412225_Union Executive of India_ Structure, Powers, Roles, and Functions.pdf', 'The Union Executive of India comprises the President, Vice-President, Prime Minister, Council of Ministers, and Attorney General, functioning under Part V of the Constitution. It operates within a parliamentary system where the President is the constitutional head, and the Prime Minister leads the real executive. Together, they ensure administration, policy execution, law enforcement, financial governance, and national security.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(131, 'GK', 'English', 'India’s Parliament: Structure, Lawmaking, Committees, and Privileges Explained', '5', '28', '59', '8f6babc8a0524edccbc1182659d650f6.jpg', '', '1757412737_India’s Parliament_ Structure, Lawmaking, Committees, and Privileges Explained.pdf', 'India’s Parliament, comprising the President, Lok Sabha, and Rajya Sabha, is central to governance. It frames laws through a structured legislative process, aided by specialized committees. Parliamentary privileges safeguard members’ independence but face criticism for misuse and ambiguity. Key judicial rulings and reforms aim to balance these privileges with transparency, accountability, and the democratic spirit.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(132, 'GK', 'English', 'Judiciary in India: Balancing Activism, Restraint, and Constitutional Mandates', '5', '28', '59', 'be1cac4a648d4af9bb2741af4b4254e2.png', '', '1757413505_Judiciary in India_ Balancing Activism, Restraint, and Constitutional Mandates.pdf', 'The Indian judiciary plays a pivotal role in safeguarding constitutional rights through judicial review, activism, and restraint. While activism advances rights and fills legislative gaps, overreach risks undermining separation of powers. Landmark cases like Kesavananda Bharati, Maneka Gandhi, and Vishaka shaped public law, highlighting the judiciary’s role in democracy, yet emphasizing the need for principled limits.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2025-10-04 13:38:50'),
(133, 'GK', 'English', 'Constitutional Role, Powers, and Challenges of India’s State Governors', '5', '28', '60', '8c9186b25f7ecea9603e9ce1c3223c58.jpg', '', '1757413747_Constitutional Role, Powers, and Challenges of India’s State Governors.pdf', 'The Governor, India’s constitutional head of state, bridges the Centre and State. Appointed by the President, the role carries executive, legislative, and judicial powers, balanced by constitutional conventions and judicial rulings. While intended as a neutral office, controversies over political bias, misuse of Article 356, and delayed bill assent persist, prompting calls for reforms and stricter accountability.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(134, 'GK', 'English', 'Chief Minister and Council: Pillars of India’s State Governance', '5', '28', '60', 'a681913d0730d53e33d06740e29c732c.png', '', '1757415167_Chief Minister and Council_ Pillars of India’s State Governance.pdf', 'The Chief Minister and Council of Ministers form the real executive at the state level, guiding policy, legislation, and administration within India’s federal framework. Appointed by the Governor, they operate under collective and individual responsibility to the Legislative Assembly. Bound by constitutional provisions, they ensure governance continuity, uphold democratic principles, and act as the state’s decision-making core.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(135, 'GK', 'English', 'Bicameral State Legislatures: Structure, Powers, and Role in India', '5', '28', '60', '9bdeaedf4cd834af8f6a2016de95351a.jpg', '', '1757415318_Bicameral State Legislatures_ Structure, Powers, and Role in India.pdf', 'India’s federal system grants states legislative bodies that may be unicameral or bicameral. Six states have Legislative Councils alongside Assemblies, serving as review chambers. Governed by Articles 169, 171, and 172, these councils scrutinize laws, represent experts, and maintain political continuity, though with limited powers compared to assemblies. Their creation or abolition requires Parliament’s approval after state resolution.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(136, 'GK', 'English', 'High and Subordinate Courts: Structure, Powers, and Constitutional Role', '5', '28', '60', '4c4d9a0a2c08757495c9399853649883.png', '', '1757416514_High and Subordinate Courts_ Structure, Powers, and Constitutional Role.pdf', 'India’s judicial system follows a single, integrated hierarchy with High Courts as the top authority in states and Subordinate Courts as the grassroots level of justice. High Courts ensure constitutional compliance, fundamental rights protection, and appellate review, while Subordinate Courts handle day-to-day civil, criminal, and revenue disputes. Both face challenges like backlog, vacancies, and infrastructure gaps.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(137, 'GK', 'English', '73rd Amendment: Strengthening Panchayati Raj for Grassroots Democracy in India', '5', '28', '61', '3eb77de8f5773f812294bfd29b991cd5.jpeg', '', '1757418169_73rd Amendment_ Strengthening Panchayati Raj for Grassroots Democracy in India.pdf', 'The 73rd Constitutional Amendment Act, 1992 institutionalized Panchayati Raj, ensuring democratic decentralization in rural India through a three-tier system, Gram Sabhas, reservations, and State Election/Finance Commissions. Covering 29 subjects in the 11th Schedule, it empowered local bodies but faces challenges like uneven devolution, fiscal dependence, and limited capacity. Strengthening PRIs is vital for inclusive, participatory rural governance.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(138, 'GK', 'English', 'Empowering Cities: The 74th Constitutional Amendment Reshapes Urban Governance', '5', '28', '61', '614931fc42822551dbcc48888e788926.jpg', '', '1757418320_Empowering Cities_ The 74th Constitutional Amendment Reshapes Urban Governance.pdf', 'The 74th Constitutional Amendment Act, 1992 granted constitutional status to municipalities, institutionalizing urban local governance in India. By adding Part IX-A and the Twelfth Schedule, it defined structures, powers, functions, and finances of Urban Local Bodies. It sought to strengthen grassroots democracy, enhance citizen participation, and improve urban administration, though implementation has varied significantly across states.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(139, 'GK', 'English', 'Strengthening Local Governance: Challenges, Reforms, and Pathways to Empowerment', '5', '28', '61', 'ea0c7928ed679fb0dbd532097cb1a75f.jpg', '', '1757494295_Strengthening Local Governance_ Challenges, Reforms, and Pathways to Empowerment.pdf', 'Local governance in India faces significant challenges, including inadequate fiscal autonomy, capacity gaps, political interference, and poor citizen participation. Despite constitutional provisions, many state governments delay decentralization, limiting the efficiency of urban and rural bodies. Strengthening legal frameworks, enhancing financial independence, building institutional capacity, and integrating technology are vital to ensure transparent, inclusive, and sustainable local governance.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(140, 'GK', 'English', 'Union Territories: Constitutional framework, governance challenges, reforms and current issues', '5', '28', '62', '6b4db510f858b6c648c356b95fb3c555.jpg', '', '1757494462_Union Territories_ Constitutional framework, governance challenges, reforms and current issues.pdf', 'Union Territories (UTs) are centrally administered units under Articles 239–241, each headed by an Administrator or Lieutenant Governor. Some UTs—Delhi, Puducherry, Jammu & Kashmir—have legislatures with limited powers, while others are directly governed by the Centre. Despite their strategic roles, UTs face democratic deficits, frequent Centre–local disputes, and structural fragility, prompting calls for reforms in governance, autonomy, and representation.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(141, 'GK', 'English', 'Fifth and Sixth Schedules: Constitutional Safeguards for India’s Tribal Areas', '5', '28', '62', '489174e5d11029d6ea2c10d5b7542437.jpg', '', '1757494592_Fifth and Sixth Schedules_ Constitutional Safeguards for India’s Tribal Areas.pdf', 'India’s Constitution safeguards tribal regions through the Fifth and Sixth Schedules. The Fifth Schedule governs Scheduled Areas in ten states via Governor’s regulations, Tribes Advisory Councils, and PESA powers for Gram Sabhas. The Sixth Schedule creates Autonomous Councils in select Northeastern states with legislative, executive, judicial, and fiscal authority. Both aim to protect tribal land, culture, and self-governance amid evolving challenges.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(142, 'GK', 'English', 'Election Commission & State Commissions: Constitutional Role, Structure, Powers, Reforms', '5', '28', '63', 'd411587e71e00a990eead4e84201133f.jpg', '', '1757494795_Election Commission & State Commissions_ Constitutional Role, Structure, Powers, Reforms.pdf', 'The Election Commission of India (ECI) under Article 324 oversees parliamentary, state legislature, and presidential elections, while State Election Commissions (SECs) under Articles 243K and 243ZA conduct local body polls. This article explains their constitutional basis, powers, composition, appointment reforms, case laws, and independence safeguards, along with challenges like appointment controversies, transparency debates, and delays in local elections.Election Commission of India (ECI) was established on 25 January 1950.State Election Commissions (SECs) were established in 1993\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(143, 'GK', 'English', 'UPSC and State PSCs: Structure, Powers, Functions, Constitutional Safeguards', '5', '28', '63', '866a07e3e49c8ba9d2901749dd24b8e0.jpeg', '', '1757494927_Election Commission & State Commissions_ Constitutional Role, Structure, Powers, Reforms.pdf', 'The Union Public Service Commission (UPSC) and State Public Service Commissions (SPSCs) are independent constitutional bodies established under Articles 315–323 of Part XIV. UPSC recruits for Union and All-India Services, while SPSC recruits for State services. With secure tenure, removal safeguards, financial autonomy, and defined consultative roles, they ensure merit-based recruitment, uphold administrative integrity, and maintain transparent selection processes across government services.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(144, 'GK', 'English', '', '5', '28', '63', '8d6d4c64a954ac856cb6540a08e75204.jpg', '', '1759570047_PUblished - Finance Commission_ Fiscal federalism, devolution, challenges, and future directions.pdf', 'The Finance Commission, a constitutional body under Article 280, defines Union–State fiscal relations every five years. It recommends tax devolution, grants-in-aid, and resource allocation principles. While its role is central to cooperative federalism, challenges remain—data gaps, political economy pressures, and implementation delays. The 16th Commission, chaired by Arvind Panagariya. \r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2025-10-04 14:57:27'),
(145, 'GK', 'English', 'Comptroller and Auditor General: Guardian of India’s Public Financial Accountability', '5', '28', '63', 'bdc0646910c7ae31fe9709534583f931.jpg', '', '1757495312_Comptroller and Auditor General_ Guardian of India’s Public Financial Accountability.pdf', 'The Comptroller and Auditor General (CAG) of India, established under Article 148,which came into effect on 26 January 1950. audits all receipts, expenditure, and accounts of the Union and States. Appointed by the President for six years or until 65 years, the CAG ensures transparency, accountability, and fiscal discipline. Its reports influence parliamentary oversight and strengthen India’s democratic governance by monitoring financial integrity.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `post_gk` (`id`, `post_type`, `langu`, `title`, `category`, `subcategory`, `section`, `image`, `image_link`, `documnet_link`, `description`, `created`, `updated`) VALUES
(146, 'GK', 'English', 'Guardians of justice: NCSC, NCST and NCBC in action', '5', '28', '63', 'f8a2d7516ea3d9ca5b0b2345c12498b0.jpg', '', '1757495495_Guardians of justice_ NCSC, NCST and NCBC in action.pdf', 'The National Commission for Scheduled Castes (Art. 338), Scheduled Tribes (Art. 338A) and Backward Classes (Art. 338B) safeguard constitutional rights of vulnerable communities. They investigate complaints, monitor legal safeguards, advise governments, and report to the President. Originating from constitutional amendments, these bodies now face capacity and coordination challenges but remain vital to social justice in India.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(147, 'GK', 'English', 'NITI Aayog: Driving India’s Inclusive Growth through Cooperative Federalism', '5', '28', '64', 'f60e75aba6a51bcd98e1de21df49126a.jpg', '', '1757495785_NITI Aayog_ Driving India’s Inclusive Growth through Cooperative Federalism.pdf', 'Established on January 1, 2015, NITI Aayog replaced the Planning Commission as India’s apex public policy think tank. Led by the Prime Minister, it fosters cooperative and competitive federalism, drives innovation, monitors SDGs, and implements transformative initiatives like the Aspirational Districts and Blocks Programmes. Through strategic vision, data-driven governance, and state engagement, it aims to achieve Viksit Bharat @2047.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(148, 'GK', 'English', 'NHRC, SHRCs & Coordinated Commissions: Mandate, Limitations, Strengthening Institutional Synergy', '5', '28', '64', '4f355aae0ae0b2868e69f3056aa9fda7.jpg', '', '1757498287_NHRC, SHRCs & Coordinated Commissions_ Mandate, Limitations, Strengthening Institutional Synergy.pdf', 'The NHRC (1993, amended 2006 & 2019) and SHRCs safeguard constitutional rights—life, liberty, equality, and dignity. They can investigate violations with civil-court powers, visit institutions, and recommend reliefs. Constraints include time-bar, non-binding orders, and limited armed-forces jurisdiction. The NHRC now collaborates with seven national commissions to streamline policy, research, and enforcement. Reforms focus on greater independence, proactive mandates, resources, legal powers, and public outreach.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(149, 'GK', 'English', 'Central Vigilance Commission: India’s independent statutory anti-corruption oversight body', '5', '28', '64', '017599d26f128238b38b44afb5bc7f50.png', '', '1757498748_Central Vigilance Commission_ India’s independent statutory anti-corruption oversight body.pdf', 'The Central Vigilance Commission (CVC), established in 1964 on Santhanam Committee’s recommendation and granted statutory status by the CVC Act, 2003, is India’s apex vigilance body. It supervises vigilance administration in Union Government organisations, oversees CBI investigations under the Prevention of Corruption Act, advises on disciplinary actions, monitors procurement integrity, and safeguards whistleblowers. Independent of executive control, it reports directly to Parliament.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(150, 'GK', 'English', 'India’s Lokpal & Lokayuktas: Statutory Anti-Corruption Watchdogs Ensuring Accountability', '5', '28', '64', '4e80a90eebe8aaf0b7f1fa883e3f4718.jpg', '', '1757498845_India’s Lokpal & Lokayuktas_ Statutory Anti-Corruption Watchdogs Ensuring Accountability.pdf', 'The Lokpal and Lokayuktas Act, 2013 mandates statutory ombudsmen at both Union (Lokpal) and State (Lokayukta) levels to investigate corruption by public functionaries. Enacted on 1 January and effective from 16 January 2014, Lokpal’s jurisdiction spans the Prime Minister (with narrow exceptions), Ministers, MPs, and all Group A–D officials. States must similarly establish Lokayuktas under their own laws. \r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(151, 'GK', 'English', 'National Emergency in India: Constitutional grounds, procedure, effects, safeguards', '5', '28', '65', 'abacabd26adacd63b6bdf4bc3d58c516.jpeg', '', '1757498956_National Emergency in India_ Constitutional grounds, procedure, effects, safeguards.pdf', 'A National Emergency (Article 352) may be proclaimed by the President when India’s security is threatened by war, external aggression, or armed rebellion. The 44th Amendment introduced safeguards—written Cabinet advice, special majority within one month, six-month renewals, and Lok Sabha disapproval power. It alters Centre–State powers, affects Fundamental Rights (Arts. 358–359), and has been declared thrice: 1962, 1971, and 1975.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(152, 'GK', 'English', 'State Emergency: Article 356 and President’s Rule in India', '5', '28', '65', 'ff384a20b3a167581515c55d23bccdf8.jpg', '', '1757499887_State Emergency_ Article 356 and President’s Rule in India.pdf', 'Article 356 empowers the President to impose President’s Rule in a state if its constitutional machinery fails. It suspends the state government and transfers legislative and executive powers to the Centre. Although intended as a safeguard, its misuse for political purposes has drawn criticism. Judicial review and constitutional amendments now regulate its imposition.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(153, 'GK', 'English', 'Financial Emergency: Powers, Procedure, Effects, Safeguards under Article 360', '5', '28', '65', '1927c60a95e23c57ffecbb7de9d80a6c.jpg', '', '1757500081_Financial Emergency_ Powers, Procedure, Effects, Safeguards under Article 360.pdf', 'Article 360 empowers the President to proclaim a Financial Emergency if India’s financial stability or credit is threatened. Parliament must approve it within two months. It authorises Union directions to States, salary cuts (including judges), and reservation of State Money Bills for Presidential consideration. No such emergency has ever been declared. The 44th Amendment restored judicial review over the proclamation.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(154, 'GK', 'English', 'Centre–State Legislative Relations: Constitutional framework, powers, and conflict resolution', '5', '28', '66', 'be92be7ad7839feaadb8f48c33546c33.jpg', '', '1757500314_Centre–State Legislative Relations_ Constitutional framework, powers, and conflict resolution.pdf', 'Legislative relations in India, governed by Part XI (Articles 245–255) and the Seventh Schedule, define the law-making powers of Parliament and State Legislatures. The Constitution outlines territorial extent, distribution of subjects, special circumstances for Parliament’s intervention in the State List, and Centre’s control over State laws. Federal balance is maintained through doctrines, emergency provisions, and constitutional safeguards.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(155, 'GK', 'English', 'Centre–State Administrative Relations: Powers, Duties, Coordination, and Emergency Controls', '5', '28', '66', '81942bb81c1bb16ccf3fb23aa4aaa581.jpg', '', '1757500905_Centre–State Administrative Relations_ Powers, Duties, Coordination, and Emergency Controls.pdf', 'Administrative Relations under the Indian Constitution govern the distribution and coordination of executive powers between the Union and States. Rooted in Articles 73, 162, and 256–263, they cover obligations of States, Union directions, mutual delegation, All India Services, Public Service Commissions, and intergovernmental mechanisms. These relations shift during emergencies, while commissions and councils promote cooperative federalism and resolve disputes.', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(156, 'GK', 'English', 'Centre–State Financial Relations: Taxation, Revenue Sharing, Grants, and Fiscal Control', '5', '28', '66', '16c393fc7ca3c175415835ca3c3798df.jpg', '', '1757500979_Centre–State Financial Relations_ Taxation, Revenue Sharing, Grants, and Fiscal Control.pdf', 'The Indian Constitution’s Part XII (Articles 265–293) governs Centre–State financial relations, covering taxation powers, revenue distribution, grants, and borrowing limits. Taxing authority is split between Union and States, with GST introducing concurrent powers. The Finance Commission drives devolution, while Articles 275 and 282 govern grants. Persistent debates include vertical/horizontal imbalances, cesses, GST autonomy, and emergency fiscal powers.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(157, 'GK', 'English', 'Revitalising India\'s Federalism: Inter-State Council & Zonal Councils Dynamics', '5', '28', '66', 'e2811b80db57b22e0f5e5e6ab1cb5a13.jpg', '', '1757502376_Revitalising India\'s Federalism_ Inter-State Council & Zonal Councils Dynamics.pdf', 'India’s federal architecture features two pivotal consultative bodies: the constitutional Inter-State Council (ISC) under Article 263, and the statutory Zonal Councils (ZCs) under the States Reorganisation Act, 1956. The ISC, chaired by the Prime Minister, was recently reconstituted in 2024 to reinforce Centre–State dialogue. The ZCs, led by the Home Minister, address regional cooperation across five zones. Both reinforce cooperative federalism while preserving state autonomy.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(158, 'GK', 'English', 'Jammu & Kashmir: Transformation Before and After Article 370 Removal', '5', '28', '67', '1d20e6a3921cb95135231b15f777e0d8.jpg', '', '1757502514_Jammu & Kashmir_ Transformation Before and After Article 370 Removal.pdf', 'Article 370 granted Jammu & Kashmir special autonomy within India, shaping its governance, citizenship, and property laws. On 5 August 2019, the Government of India revoked this status, reorganizing the state into two Union Territories—Jammu & Kashmir and Ladakh. The move altered its constitutional position, legal structure, and political landscape, sparking national and international debate.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(159, 'GK', 'English', 'Special Provisions for Indian States: Constitutional Safeguards under Articles 371–371J', '5', '28', '67', '7b1d92bf1d86c3ee1d029263b5d3a6e2.jpeg', '', '1757502753_Special Provisions for Indian States_ Constitutional Safeguards under Articles 371–371J.pdf', 'The Indian Constitution grants special provisions to several states under Articles 371 to 371J to address historical, cultural, and developmental needs. These include protection of tribal rights, preservation of local customs, and promotion of regional development. While ensuring national unity, these provisions recognize India’s diversity. Recent debates question their relevance in a rapidly modernizing and integrated India.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(160, 'GK', 'English', 'Constitutional vs. Statutory Tribunals: Authority, Structure, and Judicial Oversight', '5', '28', '68', 'c3d0b886cbbcef6c146bc84e02ac3ba0.jpeg', '', '1757502986_Constitutional vs. Statutory Tribunals_ Authority, Structure, and Judicial Oversight.pdf', 'Tribunals in India are quasi-judicial bodies designed to reduce the burden on regular courts and provide specialized justice. They are classified into Constitutional Tribunals, directly established under the Constitution, and Statutory Tribunals, created through Parliamentary or State laws. While both aim at speedy dispute resolution, their establishment, powers, and scope differ significantly, making this distinction vital for understanding Indian administrative justice.Constitutional recognition with the 42nd Constitutional Amendment, 1976\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(161, 'GK', 'English', 'Tribunals in India: Constitutional role, reforms, Ordinance, and challenges', '5', '28', '68', '9fe3a1654017091cc160d55c6fef15d0.jpg', '', '1757505044_Tribunals in India_ Constitutional role, reforms, Ordinance, and challenges.pdf', 'Tribunals, rooted in Articles 323A/323B, deliver specialized justice outside regular courts. From the ITAT (1941) to sectoral tribunals, their evolution saw judicial scrutiny in Sampath Kumar (1987), L. Chandra Kumar (1997), and Rojer Mathew (2019). The Tribunals Reforms Ordinance, 2021, followed by the Act, abolished several tribunals, transferred powers to High Courts, and redefined appointments—sparking debates on independence, tenure, and effectiveness.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(162, 'GK', 'English', 'India’s Official Language Policy: Evolution, Safeguards, Judiciary, and Diversity', '5', '28', '69', '5f9fdd3b5a42c202635ee7295f9c67da.jpeg', '', '1757506206_India’s Official Language Policy_ Evolution, Safeguards, Judiciary, and Diversity.pdf', 'Part XVII of the Constitution (Articles 343–351) governs India’s official language policy: Hindi in Devanagari as Union’s official language, with English continuing by law. States adopt their own languages, courts primarily use English, and safeguards protect linguistic minorities. The Eighth Schedule expanded from 14 to 22 languages. Special directives, commissions, and the Official Languages Act (1963/1967) ensure linguistic balance.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(163, 'GK', 'English', 'India’s Official Language Debates and Eighth Schedule: History, Provisions, Future', '5', '28', '69', '2127383bbb119fa650764ef720684e5a.jpeg', '', '1757507092_India’s Official Language Debates and Eighth Schedule_ History, Provisions, Future.pdf', 'India’s language policy, rooted in Articles 343–351, made Hindi (Devanagari) the Union’s official language in 1950, with English continuing through the Official Languages Act, 1963 (amended 1967). The Eighth Schedule began with 14 languages, later expanded—Sindhi (1967), Konkani/Manipuri/Nepali (1992), Bodo/Dogri/Maithili/Santali (2004). In 2011, “Oriya” became “Odia.” Today, 22 languages enjoy constitutional recognition, while demands for inclusion of Bhojpuri, Rajasthani, Tulu, and others remain pending.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(164, 'GK', 'English', 'Electoral Reforms in India: Challenges, measures, and democratic strengthening', '5', '28', '70', '04c240e827c68cc04d323b28037b6c2e.jpg', '', '1757580551_Electoral Reforms in India_ Challenges, measures, and democratic strengthening.pdf', 'Electoral reforms in India aim to enhance transparency, fairness, and participation in the democratic process. From anti-defection laws and voting age reduction to EVMs and NOTA, reforms address corruption, criminalization, and voter apathy. Despite progress, challenges like money power, paid news, and electoral bonds persist. Continuous reforms remain crucial for ensuring free, fair, and credible elections in the world’s largest democracy.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(165, 'GK', 'English', 'Anti-Defection Law in India: Origins, Provisions, Cases, Reforms', '5', '28', '70', '598c8a13b06495f734342f2968a55201.jpg', '', '1757580743_Anti-Defection Law in India_ Origins, Provisions, Cases, Reforms.pdf', 'The Anti-Defection Law, introduced via the 52nd Amendment (1985) and strengthened by the 91st Amendment (2003), seeks to prevent instability caused by legislators switching parties. Disqualification applies for voluntarily giving up membership, defying whips, or post-election party-joining by independents/nominated members. While it curbs horse-trading, critics highlight curtailed debate freedom and partisan delays by Speakers. Reforms suggest independent adjudication and limited whip application.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(166, 'GK', 'English', 'Representation of the People Act, 1950: Foundations, Rolls, Delimitation, Voting', '5', '28', '71', '254c56cd955fad06aef3e453dfa3370a.jpeg', '', '1757580917_Representation of the People Act, 1950_ Foundations, Rolls, Delimitation, Voting.pdf', 'The Representation of the People Act, 1950 establishes the electoral framework of India, covering allocation of seats, delimitation of constituencies, voter qualifications, and preparation of rolls. It empowers electoral officers, defines ordinary residence, and ensures universal adult suffrage. With provisions on overseas voters, Aadhaar linkage, and delimitation commissions, it remains vital for ensuring transparency, fairness, and inclusivity in India’s democratic process.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(167, 'GK', 'English', 'Special Leave Petition: Supreme Court’s discretionary appellate power explained', '5', '28', '71', '1c5372227f34d80e1379b0cc679c940d.jpg', '', '1757581578_Special Leave Petition_ Supreme Court’s discretionary appellate power explained.pdf', 'A Special Leave Petition (SLP) under Article 136 of the Indian Constitution empowers the Supreme Court to hear appeals from any court or tribunal, except Armed Forces bodies. It is not a matter of right but an extraordinary discretionary remedy, used sparingly to correct grave injustice or address important legal questions. The Concept of Special leave to appeal  first appeared in the Government of India Act1935.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(168, 'GK', 'English', 'Public Interest Litigation in India: Origins, evolution, impact, and challenges', '5', '28', '71', 'ca0117974e9ccd3f601f32bf493b4edc.jpg', '', '1757582511_Public Interest Litigation in India_ Origins, evolution, impact, and challenges.pdf', 'Public Interest Litigation (PIL) in India emerged in the late 1970s as a tool of judicial activism to provide justice to marginalized sections. It broadened access to courts, expanded Article 21 rights, and reshaped governance, environment, and social justice. Despite its transformative impact, PIL faces issues of misuse, judicial overreach, and docket burden, requiring balanced reforms.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(169, 'GK', 'English', 'Right to Information Act: Empowering Citizens through Transparency and Accountability', '5', '28', '71', '37fd74f8c445990921e9875b44f9de3a.jpg', '', '1757582715_Right to Information Act_ Empowering Citizens through Transparency and Accountability.pdf', 'The Right to Information Act, 2005, is a landmark legislation ensuring transparency, accountability, and citizen participation in governance. By granting access to public records, it empowers individuals to question authorities and curb corruption. Rooted in Article 19(1)(a) of the Constitution, the Act strengthens democracy, promotes good governance, and holds government institutions accountable to the people.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(170, 'GK', 'English', 'Recent Supreme Court Judgments: Shaping Democracy, Rights, and Governance in India', '5', '28', '72', '08cff25ed0cafe89170ea0f9a07f8ec1.jpg', '', '1757583709_Recent Supreme Court Judgments_ Shaping Democracy, Rights, and Governance in India.pdf', 'The Supreme Court of India has delivered landmark rulings in 2023–25 on electoral reforms, federalism, environmental governance, education integrity, and criminal justice reforms. From striking down electoral bonds to clarifying due process in demolitions and guiding NEET exams, these verdicts shape constitutional values and governance.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(171, 'GK', 'English', 'Major Constitutional Amendments: Shaping India’s Democracy Through Law and Reform', '5', '28', '72', '2134eccf5272612448c4a587af5ad4a6.jpg', '', '1757583914_Major Constitutional Amendments_ Shaping India’s Democracy Through Law and Reform.pdf', 'The Indian Constitution, both flexible and rigid, has been amended over time to reflect social change, economic needs, and political reforms. From the 1st Amendment’s protection of land reforms to the 42nd “Mini Constitution,” and the 106th Amendment reserving seats for women in legislatures, these changes showcase India’s evolving democracy. Each amendment embodies constitutional morality, balancing rights, duties, and governance needs.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(172, 'GK', 'English', 'Major Governance Bills and Acts Reshaping India’s Administrative and Legal Framework', '5', '28', '72', 'a81b1ff194aaaed8daa431d5ee6dae99.png', '', '1757584327_Major Governance Bills and Acts Reshaping India’s Administrative and Legal Framework.pdf', 'From digital governance to women’s rights, Parliament has passed several transformative bills since 2019. Key enactments include the Digital Personal Data Protection Act, 2023, Women’s Reservation Act, 2023, and Criminal Law reforms, 2023–24. Each reflects India’s evolving governance needs, balancing efficiency, accountability, and citizen-centric reforms. \r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(173, 'GK', 'English', 'Evolving Federalism in India: Emerging Tensions, Challenges, and Cooperative Pathways', '5', '28', '72', '332f63a4970d509ecef3f26fed1d4a1f.jpeg', '', '1757585819_Evolving Federalism in India_ Emerging Tensions, Challenges, and Cooperative Pathways.pdf', 'India’s federalism faces recurring strains over fiscal autonomy, legislative overreach, and political partisanship. Issues like GST compensation disputes, Governor–state tussles, abrogation of Article 370, and river water conflicts highlight a centralizing trend. Yet, cooperative frameworks—GST Council, NITI Aayog, Inter-State Council—offer avenues for dialogue. Understanding these tensions is crucial for governance, democracy, and Centre–state balance.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(174, 'GK', 'English', 'The President of India: Powers, Election, Functions, and Constitutional Role', '5', '29', '73', '3e5f2d2466046c71b31879efe6478301.png', '', '1757587360_The President of India_ Powers, Election, Functions, and Constitutional Role.pdf', 'The President of India, as the constitutional head and first citizen, symbolizes national unity and safeguards democracy. Elected through an Electoral College, the President wields executive, legislative, financial, judicial, and emergency powers while bound by ministerial advice. Though often a nominal head, the office becomes crucial during crises, ensuring stability, constitutional governance, and balance within India’s parliamentary system.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(175, 'GK', 'English', 'Prime Minister of India: Appointment, Powers, Functions and Importance', '5', '29', '74', '15c8c05efd8f1eebc86c760476745e1d.png', '', '1757587565_Prime Minister of India_ Appointment, Powers, Functions and Importance.pdf', 'The Prime Minister of India is the real executive authority in the parliamentary system, appointed by the President but dependent on the confidence of the Lok Sabha. As head of the Council of Ministers, the PM directs governance, policy, finance, foreign affairs, and security. Through leadership, coordination, and accountability, the PM ensures democratic functioning while operating within constitutional, legal, and federal limits.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(176, 'GK', 'English', 'Indian Parliament: Structure, Powers, Functions, Role in Democratic Governance', '5', '29', '75', '1bb3f09e637da7689016404a869bfd0c.jpg', '', '1757587836_Indian Parliament_ Structure, Powers, Functions, Role in Democratic Governance.pdf', 'The Indian Parliament, comprising the President, Lok Sabha, and Rajya Sabha, is the cornerstone of democratic governance. It enacts laws, controls finances, and holds the executive accountable through debates, questions, and committees. With bicameral structure, federal balance, and constitutional safeguards like anti-defection rules and joint sittings, Parliament ensures representation, deliberation, and stability while evolving through reforms such as women’s reservation.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(177, 'GK', 'English', 'Indian Judiciary: Structure, Powers, and Roles of Supreme, High Courts', '5', '29', '51', '0425f9274beede57f16eb7286130de1f.png', '', '1757589006_Indian Judiciary_ Structure, Powers, and Roles of Supreme, High Courts.pdf', 'India’s judiciary, a unified and independent system, is headed by the Supreme Court and supported by High Courts in states and subordinate courts. The Supreme Court enforces fundamental rights, interprets the Constitution, and settles Union-State disputes. High Courts exercise broad writ powers, supervise subordinate courts, and safeguard justice at the state level. Together, they uphold constitutional supremacy, rights, and democracy.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(178, 'GK', 'English', 'Indian Federalism: Division of Powers Among Union, States, Local Governments', '5', '29', '52', '8d7c6e3e1b6e811ba28fd179af96deca.png', '', '1757589106_Indian Federalism_ Division of Powers Among Union, States, Local Governments.pdf', 'Indian federalism rests on a structured division of legislative, administrative and financial powers across Union, States and local governments. The Constitution’s Seventh Schedule, Part XI, and key amendments (73rd, 74th, 101st) define this balance. Institutions like the Finance Commission, Inter-State Council and GST Council strengthen cooperative federalism, though tensions arise from fiscal dependence, centralisation and uneven local governance.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(179, 'GK', 'English', 'Elections and Political Parties in India: Process, Role, Significance', '5', '29', '78', '008f37787f86b21e001dd9606081e1be.png', '', '1757589254_Elections and Political Parties in India_ Process, Role, Significance.pdf', 'Elections form the backbone of India’s democracy, ensuring citizen participation and accountability. Conducted by the Election Commission under constitutional and statutory provisions, they translate public will into governance. Political parties aggregate interests, recruit leaders, and mobilize voters. However, money power, criminalization, misinformation, and weak regulation remain challenges. Strengthening transparency, electoral rolls, party democracy, and finance reforms are essential to safeguard democratic resilience.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(180, 'GK', 'English', 'Government Policies and Schemes: Driving India’s Inclusive Growth and Development', '5', '30', '54', '93175031a75f38c868abc3db450bc8e0.jpg', '', '1757589385_Government Policies and Schemes_ Driving India’s Inclusive Growth and Development.pdf', 'Government policies and schemes in India play a pivotal role in inclusive development by addressing health, housing, water, sanitation, employment, and infrastructure gaps. Flagship missions like Ayushman Bharat, PMAY, Jal Jeevan Mission, MGNREGA, PMGSY, and Swachh Bharat have transformed welfare delivery. Despite successes, challenges remain in targeting, leakages, sustainability, and equitable outcomes, demanding stronger monitoring and evaluation.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(181, 'GK', 'English', 'RTI and RTE: Strengthening Transparency and Access to Education', '5', '30', '55', '', '', '1757589708_RTI and RTE_ Strengthening Transparency and Access to Education.pdf', 'The Right to Information (RTI) Act, 2005 ensures transparency and accountability in governance, while the Right to Education (RTE) Act, 2009 guarantees free, compulsory schooling for children aged 6–14. Together, they empower citizens and safeguard children’s rights. RTI strengthens RTE by exposing inefficiencies, enabling social audits, and ensuring that education rights are enforced in practice.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(182, 'GK', 'English', 'Panchayati Raj in India: Evolution, Structure, Challenges, and Democratic Role', '5', '30', '56', '1f6ebe840bd0957f26dfc2ec4347aa09.jpeg', '', '1757589819_Panchayati Raj in India_ Evolution, Structure, Challenges, and Democratic Role.pdf', 'The Panchayati Raj system, formalised by the 73rd Constitutional Amendment (1992), institutionalises grassroots democracy through a three-tier structure — Gram Panchayat, Panchayat Samiti, and Zilla Parishad. It covers 29 subjects under the Eleventh Schedule and mandates elections, reservations, and Gram Sabha participation. Despite successes in decentralisation, Panchayats face challenges of inadequate devolution, financial weakness, and social inequalities, demanding further reforms.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(183, 'GK', 'English', 'Measuring India’s GDP: Growth Trends, Challenges, and Development Insights', '6', '31', '82', 'e71666a249e4d9692cfd3450b9f47d98.jpg', '', '1757592353_Measuring India’s GDP_ Growth Trends, Challenges, and Development Insights.pdf', 'Gross Domestic Product (GDP) is the total monetary value of all final goods and services produced within a country’s borders during a specific period (usually a quarter or a year), irrespective of who owns the production resources.India’s Gross Domestic Product (GDP) reflects the scale and dynamics of its economy, serving as a key measure of growth and development. Compiled by the National Statistical Office, GDP highlights sectoral strengths, expenditure patterns, and investment drivers. \r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(184, 'GK', 'English', 'Gross National Product: Measuring National Income in a Globalized World', '6', '31', '83', 'e0d88d0d76011e440ad08581e19f1d0c.jpg', '', '1757592508_Gross National Product_ Measuring National Income in a Globalized World.pdf', 'Gross National Product (GNP), also known as Gross National Income (GNI), is defined as the total monetary value of all final goods and services produced by a nation’s residents, regardless of location, during a given year. Mathematically, GNP = GDP + Net Factor Income from Abroad (NFIA). It captures residents’ income better than GDP in today’s globalized economy of migration, FDI, and cross-border financial flows.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(185, 'GK', 'English', 'Net National Product: Economic Indicator Measuring National Wealth and Growth', '6', '31', '84', '6ee92df7815465aff7a28175935ff3de.png', '', '1757593501_“Net National Product_ Economic Indicator Measuring National Wealth and Growth”.pdf', 'Net National Product (NNP) is the total market value of all final goods and services produced by a country’s residents in a year, after accounting for depreciation of capital. NNP is a key indicator of economic performance, showing net production, guiding policy decisions, investment planning, and international economic comparisons, while highlighting the nation’s sustainable wealth generation capacity.', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(186, 'GK', 'English', 'Net Domestic Product: Measuring Sustainable Economic Growth and Capital Utilization', '6', '31', '85', 'ab6365aef6850b3dfd6b3eebd93144ba.png', '', '1757666875_Net Domestic Product_ Measuring Sustainable Economic Growth and Capital Utilization.pdf', 'Net Domestic Product (NDP) is the total market value of all final goods and services produced within a country, minus depreciation of capital assets. It indicates the sustainable economic output by showing how much of GDP remains after accounting for capital consumption. NDP helps policymakers, students, and researchers assess long-term growth and investment needs effectively.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(187, 'GK', 'English', 'Role of Money: Functions, Types, Importance, and Economic Stability Explained', '6', '31', '86', 'fc962cdfafd42de51192a495cf7c2d72.jpg', '', '1757667175_Role of Money_ Functions, Types, Importance, and Economic Stability Explained.pdf', 'Money is any widely accepted medium of exchange, serving as a unit of account, store of value, and standard for deferred payments. It facilitates trade, investment, and economic stability by influencing resource allocation, consumption, and fiscal policies. Its types include commodity, fiat, and digital money, each supporting diverse economic functions effectively.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(188, 'GK', 'English', 'Inflation in India: Causes, Consequences, and Government Control Measures', '6', '31', '87', '3b4e6c1239f780845d7ef20193643d90.jpeg', '', '1757667300_Inflation in India_ Causes, Consequences, and Government Control Measures.pdf', 'Inflation is the sustained rise in the general price level, reducing the purchasing power of money. In India, inflation is measured mainly through CPI and WPI. It arises from demand pressures, supply shocks, food price volatility, and global factors. Its effects range from eroding savings to reducing competitiveness. Government and RBI control inflation using monetary, fiscal, and supply-side measures.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(189, 'GK', 'English', 'Deflation in India: Causes, Impacts, Risks, and Policy Responses', '6', '31', '88', 'c07592d13535a030d7035dab2cc81f7c.jpg', '', '1757667476_Deflation in India_ Causes, Impacts, Risks, and Policy Responses.pdf', 'Deflation is a sustained fall in the general price level of goods and services. Though rare in India, it can occur due to weak demand, falling food prices, or global disinflation. Deflation risks include higher debt burdens, unemployment, and slower growth. Policymakers respond through monetary easing, fiscal stimulus, and structural safeguards to stabilize demand and maintain economic growth.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(190, 'GK', 'English', 'India’s Fiscal Policy: Spending, Tax Reforms, Growth, and Fiscal Consolidation', '6', '31', '89', '3aa1ec4c370a06b3665e17effd383ba3.jpg', '', '1757668487_India’s Fiscal Policy_ Spending, Tax Reforms, Growth, and Fiscal Consolidation.pdf', 'Fiscal policy refers to government decisions on spending, taxation, borrowing, and transfers to regulate growth, employment, and stability. Fiscal policy is the backbone of India’s economic strategy. It influences demand, supports welfare, builds infrastructure, and ensures inclusive growth. \r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(191, 'GK', 'English', 'RBI’s Monetary Policy: Inflation Control, Liquidity Management, and Financial Stability', '6', '31', '90', '6224c0937c2a55bfb52b1030b1241326.jpg', '', '1757668630_RBI’s Monetary Policy_ Inflation Control, Liquidity Management, and Financial Stability.pdf', 'Monetary policy is the process by which a country’s central bank, in India the Reserve Bank of India (RBI), manages money supply and credit conditions using tools like policy rates, reserve requirements, and open market operations. Its objectives are to control inflation, maintain adequate liquidity, and ensure financial stability, thereby supporting sustainable economic growth.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(192, 'GK', 'English', 'India’s Downturn: Causes, Socioeconomic Consequences, and Multi-front Recovery Strategies', '6', '31', '91', '7e5ac351c7bc2e57d6d57307904d6ab6.jpg', '', '1757669736_India’s Downturn_ Causes, Socioeconomic Consequences, and Multi-front Recovery Strategies.pdf', 'An economic downturn is a prolonged slowdown in economic activity, reflected in weaker GDP, declining consumption, reduced investment, rising unemployment, and fiscal strain. In India, downturns stem from weak demand, credit stress, external shocks, and structural constraints. They erode growth and jobs but can be mitigated through calibrated short-term stimulus, financial stability measures, and medium-to-long-term structural reforms fostering inclusive and resilient growth.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(193, 'GK', 'English', 'Two-Slab GST Reform: Simplifying Indirect Taxation for Unified India', '6', '31', '92', '909035272c1908d17c769ac567c88506.jpg', '', '1757669935_Two-Slab GST Reform_ Simplifying Indirect Taxation for Unified India.pdf', 'Definition: Indirect taxation is a tax levied on goods and services rather than income, collected at points of sale or import. GST (Goods and Services Tax) is India’s unified indirect tax, introduced in 2017, comprising CGST (Central GST), SGST (State GST), IGST (Integrated GST), and UTGST (Union Territory GST).\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(194, 'GK', 'English', 'India’s Annual Financial Statement: Budget Structure, Process, Funds, and Policy', '6', '31', '93', 'e7f3b4455a52c3008c4636f6357f14a5.jpg', '', '1757670916_India’s Annual Financial Statement_ Budget Structure, Process, Funds, and Policy.pdf', 'The Annual Financial Statement (AFS), popularly called the Union Budget, is the constitutional statement of estimated receipts and expenditures for a financial year (April 1–March 31), mandated under Article 112. It covers the Consolidated Fund, Contingency Fund, and Public Account, presenting fiscal targets, tax proposals, and expenditure plans, ensuring transparency, accountability, and resource allocation for national governance and economic growth.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(195, 'GK', 'English', 'RBI: India’s Central Bank Ensuring Monetary Discipline and Financial Stability', '6', '31', '95', '1f04cfcefbdd072c0845a121b507243a.jpg', '', '1757671688_RBI_ India’s Central Bank Ensuring Monetary Discipline and Financial Stability.pdf', 'The Reserve Bank of India (RBI), established in 1935, is India’s central bank and the primary regulator of monetary policy and financial stability. Monetary policy is the RBI’s control of money supply, credit, and interest rates to manage inflation and growth. As a regulator, RBI safeguards banks, manages currency, prevents financial crises, and promotes sustainable economic development.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(196, 'GK', 'English', 'India’s Financial Institutions: Drivers of Investment, Inclusion, and Sustainable Growth', '6', '31', '96', '9c2c51cd232770bf17e6466ae80bbfe9.jpg', '', '1757673739_India’s Financial Institutions_ Drivers of Investment, Inclusion, and Sustainable Growth.pdf', 'Financial institutions are organizations that mobilize savings, allocate credit, manage risks, and provide payment and settlement services. In India, institutions like RBI, SEBI, NABARD, SIDBI, NHB, IRDAI, PFRDA, EXIM Bank, and NPCI fuel development by funding infrastructure, supporting MSMEs and rural credit, deepening capital markets, expanding digital payments, and maintaining financial stability through supervision and reforms.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(197, 'GK', 'English', 'Modern Agriculture Practices Transforming Indian Economy, Sustainability, and Rural Livelihoods', '6', '32', '97', '0f02c09b7f16dc1ec43b86227106e486.jpg', '', '1757673901_Modern Agriculture Practices Transforming Indian Economy, Sustainability, and Rural Livelihoods.pdf', 'Modern agriculture in India integrates mechanization, precision farming, high-yield seeds, and sustainable practices, significantly boosting productivity and economic growth. It enhances farmer incomes, promotes environmental sustainability, and ensures inclusive rural development. Government initiatives and technological innovations, such as AI, digital platforms, and hydrogel innovations, address challenges like resource scarcity, climate variability, and market access, shaping a resilient agricultural future.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(198, 'GK', 'English', 'Allied Sectors Crucial for Enhancing Rural Economic Growth in India', '6', '32', '98', '958a916f1eff660f4a0af96b1d514e35.jpeg', '', '1757674073_Allied Sectors Crucial for Enhancing Rural Economic Growth in India.pdf', 'Allied sectors of agriculture are crucial for boosting rural economies in India. Beyond traditional farming, sectors such as livestock, fisheries, horticulture, agro-processing, and forestry supplement farm incomes and create alternative livelihood opportunities. Their role is significant in employment generation, poverty alleviation, and overall economic development, especially for small-scale farmers and women-headed households.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(199, 'GK', 'English', 'Industrial Development Trends Driving National Economic Growth and Global Competitiveness', '6', '32', '99', '6847f32f66f8bdf284e5a096bff5e962.jpeg', '', '1757674333_Industrial Development Trends Driving National Economic Growth and Global Competitiveness.pdf', 'Industrial development shapes national economies by enhancing employment, infrastructure, and innovation. Trends such as AI adoption, green policies, and skill development hubs are accelerating growth in India. Industrial expansion boosts GDP, exports, and trade, while strategic policies and public-private partnerships support sustainable growth. Globally, industrialization remains a key driver of economic competitiveness and prosperity.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(200, 'GK', 'English', 'Infrastructure Development Drives Economic Growth, Employment, and Regional Advancement Globally', '6', '32', '100', 'b9fc1496f9936628236e9bc23d6f264d.jpg', '', '1757674552_Infrastructure Development Drives Economic Growth, Employment, and Regional Advancement Globally.pdf', 'Infrastructure development—including transport, energy, utilities, and digital systems—is crucial for economic progress. It boosts productivity, generates employment, reduces income inequality, and promotes regional development. Both traditional and digital infrastructure significantly impact GDP growth, with benefits amplified through public-private partnerships, sustainable planning, and strategic investments. Tailored infrastructure policies maximize economic, social, and environmental outcomes worldwide.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(201, 'GK', 'English', 'Service Sector Growth Driving Employment and Economic Development in India', '6', '32', '101', 'c40f7019f2c89adbd1ddb5be4118deec.png', '', '1757677688_Service Sector Growth Driving Employment and Economic Development in India.pdf', 'India\'s service sector has become a key driver of economic growth and employment, contributing over 54% to GDP. Major sub-sectors include IT & BPO, financial services, healthcare, education, tourism, and hospitality. Employment elasticity is high, creating jobs efficiently. Challenges like skill mismatch and regional disparities exist, but government policies and digital infrastructure initiatives aim to promote inclusive growth.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(202, 'GK', 'English', 'Evaluating Poverty Alleviation Programs: Successes, Challenges, and Strategies', '6', '33', '102', '55cc2b78e6673a87d6cf1025de4b743b.jpeg', '', '1757677885_Evaluating  Poverty Alleviation Programs_ Successes, Challenges, and Strategies.pdf', 'Poverty alleviation programs in agriculture aim to improve rural livelihoods, food security, and economic stability. Evaluating their impact involves counterfactual analysis, experimental methods, and global case studies. Success depends on community engagement, tailored interventions, and robust monitoring. Despite achievements in India, China, and Nigeria, challenges like resource constraints and implementation gaps remain, highlighting the need for sustainable, context-specific strategies.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(203, 'GK', 'English', 'Empowering Rural India: Key Development Schemes Transforming Livelihoods Effectively', '6', '33', '103', '3fe67ad7fa7724552689af68881665d1.jpeg', '', '1757678017_Empowering Rural India_ Key Development Schemes Transforming Livelihoods Effectively.pdf', 'Rural development schemes in India, including DAY-NRLM, MGNREGA, PMGSY, and PMAY-G, have significantly improved livelihoods by promoting financial inclusion, employment, infrastructure, and skill development. Regional initiatives in Maharashtra and Assam highlight both successes and challenges. Despite progress, issues such as gender disparities, limited awareness, and infrastructure gaps remain, requiring focused efforts for inclusive rural empowerment and sustainable economic growth.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(204, 'GK', 'English', 'Startup India and Make in India Driving National Economic Growth', '6', '33', '104', '310a018e44913a0e91c9f0205cccd0f3.jpg', '', '1757678157_Startup India and Make in India Driving National Economic Growth.pdf', 'India’s “Startup India” and “Make in India” initiatives aim to boost entrepreneurship, manufacturing, and employment. Startup India promotes innovation and creates jobs in technology, logistics, and services. Make in India strengthens manufacturing and attracts investments. Both programs address skill gaps, regional development, and global competitiveness, while facing challenges like regulatory hurdles and infrastructure gaps, essential for economic growth.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(205, 'GK', 'English', 'Skill India Mission: Transforming Youth Skills for National Economic Growth', '6', '33', '105', '8c2ec5d62e963ebd049b7151605bc8cb.png', '', '1757678455_Skill India Mission_ Transforming Youth Skills for National Economic Growth.pdf', 'Launched in 2015, the Skill India Mission aims to equip 400 million youth with industry-relevant skills by 2023. Through initiatives like PMKVY, NAPS, and SANKALP, it enhances employability, promotes entrepreneurship, and ensures inclusive growth. By partnering with industries and focusing on emerging sectors, the mission reduces unemployment, empowers women, and strengthens India’s global workforce competitiveness.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(206, 'GK', 'English', 'Balance of Payments Trends and Economic Implications for Global Stability', '6', '34', '106', '39f83bc6a19aba1b5929560c82b3c9d0.png', '', '1757678566_Balance of Payments Trends and Economic Implications for Global Stability.pdf', 'The Balance of Payments (BOP) tracks all financial transactions between a nation and the world, including current, capital, and financial accounts. Global and Indian trends reveal fluctuations in trade balances, foreign investment, and capital flows. Persistent deficits impact currency stability, inflation, debt, and investment climate. Effective policies promoting exports, foreign investment, and economic stability are essential.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(207, 'GK', 'English', 'India’s Foreign Trade Policies Shaping Growth and Global Competitiveness', '6', '34', '107', '5c74515aefafc4002d79b7ab134dd1d0.jpg', '', '1757678755_India’s Foreign Trade Policies Shaping Growth and Global Competitiveness.pdf', 'India’s Foreign Trade Policies (FTPs) have been pivotal in boosting exports, generating employment, and enhancing industrial competitiveness. The FTP 2015–2020 focused on export growth, value addition, and employment generation, while the FTP 2023–2028 emphasizes $2 trillion export targets, digital trade, e-commerce promotion, and streamlined processes. These policies strategically align India with global trade trends.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(208, 'GK', 'English', 'Foreign Direct Investments Driving India’s Growth: FDI and FII Impact', '6', '34', '108', 'deebbd4559f06fa33aee8827af3b855f.png', '', '1757679020_Foreign Investments Driving India’s Growth_ FDI and FII Impact.pdf', 'Foreign Direct Investment (FDI) and Foreign Institutional Investment (FII) have become key drivers of India’s economic growth. They contribute to GDP, employment, technology transfer, and export enhancement. Sectors like manufacturing, IT, and financial services benefit most. Strategic policy reforms and infrastructure development ensure sustainable growth while addressing challenges like regulatory complexities and balancing domestic industry protection.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(209, 'GK', 'English', 'WTO’s Role in Shaping Global Trade Governance and Policies', '6', '34', '109', 'e80d70ee15f9dafffd9325f837a7cbdd.jpg', '', '1757680307_WTO’s Role in Shaping Global Trade Governance and Policies.pdf', 'The World Trade Organization (WTO), established in 1995, governs international trade by promoting free trade, resolving disputes, and ensuring fair competition. It administers trade agreements, facilitates negotiations, reviews national policies, and supports developing nations. Despite challenges from protectionism and regional deals, the WTO remains central to global commerce, adapting to digital trade, environmental standards, and emerging trade issues.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(213, 'GK', 'English', 'Shiva Keshavan: From Himalayan Roads to Six-Time Winter Olympian and Asian Champion', '11', '37', '119', '07772a44df31277d77e605cdef426236.jpg', '', '1758013342_Shiva Keshavan_ From Himalayan Roads to Six-Time Winter Olympian and Asian Champion.pdf', 'Shiva Keshavan, born August 25, 1981, in Manali, Himachal Pradesh, is India’s first and most celebrated luger, competing in six Winter Olympics (1998–2018), a record only surpassed by Leander Paes among Indian athletes. The youngest luger to qualify for the Olympics at 16 (Nagano 1998), he set an Asian speed record of 134.3 km/h and an Asian track record of 49.590 seconds. Keshavan won four golds (2011, 2012, 2016, 2017), four silvers (2009, 2013, 2014, 2015), and two bronzes (2005, 2008) in Asian Luge Championships and Cups. Despite limited infrastructure and funding, often relying on crowdfunding and homemade sleds, he became a global figure for resilience, earning the Arjuna Award (2020). Now retired, he serves as chief coach and High-Performance Director for India’s luge team, aiming to build winter sports infrastructure.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `post_gk` (`id`, `post_type`, `langu`, `title`, `category`, `subcategory`, `section`, `image`, `image_link`, `documnet_link`, `description`, `created`, `updated`) VALUES
(214, 'GK', 'English', 'Sajjan Singh: From Haryana’s Villages to Olympic Wrestling and Commonwealth Silver', '11', '37', '119', '0e80225940d4fbae277396e72df0714d.jpeg', '', '1758014341_Sajjan Singh_ From Haryana’s Villages to Olympic Wrestling and Commonwealth Silver.pdf', 'Sajjan Singh, born April 24, 1932, in Mahendragarh, Haryana, is a retired Indian wrestler who competed in the 1960 Rome Olympics in the men’s freestyle light heavyweight category. A standout in freestyle and Greco-Roman wrestling, he won silver in the 90 kg freestyle at the 1970 Commonwealth Games and two silvers (freestyle and Greco-Roman middleweight, 87 kg) at the 1962 Asian Games, plus a bronze in freestyle middleweight at the 1966 Asian Games. His career, rooted in Haryana’s wrestling tradition, highlighted India’s growing presence in international wrestling during the mid-20th century. Now 93, his current status is not well-documented, but he remains a notable figure in Indian wrestling history.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(215, 'GK', 'English', 'Mary D\'Souza Sequeira: From Bandra’s Tracks to Olympic Pioneer and Asian Games Medalist', '11', '37', '119', 'ed76bd32bf9d40a3246309d5db3084c6.jpg', '', '1758014993_Mary D\'Souza Sequeira_ From Bandra’s Tracks to Olympic Pioneer and Asian Games Medalist.pdf', 'Mary D\'Souza Sequeira, born July 18, 1931, in Bandra, Mumbai, is India’s first female double international, competing in track and field and field hockey. She participated in the 1952 Helsinki Olympics in the women’s 100m and 200m, among the first Indian women to compete at the Olympics. She won a bronze in the 200m and a silver in the 4x100m relay at the 1951 Asian Games, and a gold in the 4x100m relay at the 1954 Asian Games. A field hockey player, she represented India in international tournaments in 1953, 1956, 1961, and 1964. Awarded the Dhyan Chand Award in 2013, she held Asian records in the 100m and 200m in 1956. Now 94, she resides in Atlanta, USA, with her daughter Marissa Sequeira.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(216, 'GK', 'English', 'Raghbir Lal: From Punjab’s Fields to Olympic Glory in 1952 and 1956', '11', '37', '119', 'be9f7bacb4baa7c913c87827a1f1d276.jpg', '', '1758015724_Raghbir Lal_ From Punjab’s Fields to Olympic Glory in 1952 and 1956.pdf', 'Raghbir Lal Sharma (November 15, 1929 – April 7, 2025) was an Indian field hockey player who won gold medals at the 1952 Helsinki and 1956 Melbourne Olympics, contributing to India’s dominance in the sport. A right-out player for the Punjab Police team, he captained them to national titles and earned four golds and one bronze at the All-India Police Games (1952–1956). Lal played a key role in India’s undefeated 1952 Olympic campaign, scoring in the opening match, and appeared in two games, including the final, in 1956. He also toured Malaya (1954) and New Zealand (1955) with the Indian team. A Faculty of Sciences graduate, he served as a sub-inspector in the Punjab Police. Lal passed away in New Delhi at age 95.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(217, 'GK', 'English', 'Amit Singh Bakshi: From Asian Games Medals to Olympic Hockey Gold', '11', '37', '119', '85fb6a291450b557df0027b2852d7bb3.jpg', '', '1758016816_Amit Singh Bakshi_ From Asian Games Medals to Olympic Hockey Gold.pdf', 'Amit Singh Bakshi (September 17, 1925 – June 22, 2024) was an Indian athlete and field hockey player who excelled in both track and field and hockey. He won a gold medal in the men’s 4x400m relay and a silver in the 400m at the 1951 Asian Games in New Delhi. As a member of India’s field hockey team, he secured a gold medal at the 1956 Melbourne Olympics, playing in a 16-0 victory over the USA. A Wing Commander in the Indian Air Force, he later became a commercial pilot for Air India. Bakshi captained the Services team to national hockey titles in 1953 and 1956 and was a runner-up in 1954. He passed away in New Delhi at age 98.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(218, 'GK', 'English', 'Tarundeep Rai: From Sikkim’s Hills to Four-Time Olympian and Asian Games Medalist', '11', '37', '119', '15f13eece9d137d614b7644ce62eaeef.jpg', '', '1758017165_Tarundeep Rai_ From Sikkim’s Hills to Four-Time Olympian and Asian Games Medalist.pdf', 'Tarundeep Rai, born February 22, 1984, in Namchi, Sikkim, is one of India’s most accomplished archers, specializing in recurve archery. A four-time Olympian (Athens 2004, London 2012, Tokyo 2020, Paris 2024), he is the first Indian to win an individual silver medal at the Asian Games (2010). With two World Championship silvers (2005, 2019), two Asian Games medals (bronze 2006, silver 2010), and multiple World Cup medals, including a team gold in 2024, Rai has been a mainstay of Indian archery for over two decades. Awarded the Arjuna Award (2005) and Padma Shri (2021), he retired after Paris 2024 and plans to establish an archery academy in Sikkim.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(219, 'GK', 'English', 'Sajan Prakash: From Kerala’s Pools to Olympic History and National Records', '11', '37', '119', 'f7603149d41d9e679c03eb7ee98c0bdb.jpg', '', '1758017524_Sajan Prakash_ From Kerala’s Pools to Olympic History and National Records.pdf', 'Sajan Prakash, born September 14, 1993, in Idukki, Kerala, is India’s first swimmer to achieve a FINA ‘A’ Olympic qualification, securing a direct berth for the Tokyo 2020 Olympics in the 200m butterfly (1:56.38). A two-time Olympian (Rio 2016, Tokyo 2020), he holds 11 national records across freestyle, butterfly, medley, and relay events. With 6 golds at the 2015 National Games, 3 golds at the 2016 South Asian Games, and 9 medals at the 2023 National Games, he was named Best Male Athlete in 2015 and 2023. Awarded the Arjuna Award (2021), Prakash continues to compete, targeting the 2026 Commonwealth and Asian Games.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(220, 'GK', 'English', 'Srihari Nataraj: From Bengaluru’s Pools to Olympic Stages and National Records', '11', '37', '119', '11ccfd5d87087ac5d71d9cf811d0b5fc.jpg', '', '1758018218_Srihari Nataraj_ From Bengaluru’s Pools to Olympic Stages and National Records.pdf', 'Srihari Nataraj, born January 16, 2001, in Bengaluru, Karnataka, is India’s premier backstroke swimmer and a two-time Olympian (Tokyo 2020, Paris 2024). He holds national records in the 50m, 100m, and 200m backstroke, 100m and 200m freestyle, and multiple relays. With 9 golds and 1 silver at the 2025 National Games, 4 golds at the 2019 South Asian Games, and a historic FINA ‘A’ qualification for Tokyo 2020, he was named Best Male Athlete at the 2023 and 2025 National Games. Awarded the Arjuna Award (2021) and Ekalavya Award (2020), Nataraj is a trailblazer in Indian swimming.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(221, 'GK', 'English', 'Sakshi Malik: From Rohtak’s Akhara to Olympic Bronze and Social Justice Champion', '11', '37', '119', '7912328e33c530e6d4341339b34b360b.jpg', '', '1758019170_Sakshi Malik_ From Rohtak’s Akhara to Olympic Bronze and Social Justice Champion.pdf', 'Sakshi Malik, born September 3, 1992, in Mokhra, Haryana, is a former Indian freestyle wrestler who made history by winning a bronze medal in the 58kg category at the 2016 Rio Olympics, becoming India’s first female wrestler to secure an Olympic medal. With a gold at the 2022 Commonwealth Games, silvers at the 2014 Commonwealth Games and 2018 Asian Championships, and multiple international medals, she achieved a career-best world ranking of 2 (2017). Awarded the Major Dhyan Chand Khel Ratna (2016) and Padma Shri (2017), Malik retired in December 2023 after leading protests against Wrestling Federation of India (WFI) chief Brij Bhushan Sharan Singh for alleged sexual harassment. Her memoir Witness (2024) details her journey and advocacy.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(222, 'GK', 'English', 'Manika Batra: From Delhi’s Courts to Olympic and Commonwealth Glory', '11', '37', '119', '5c120c624a10ecaeef3bfeac2cb740ff.jpg', '', '1758019543_Manika Batra_ From Delhi’s Courts to Olympic and Commonwealth Glory.pdf', 'Manika Batra, born June 15, 1995, in Delhi, India, is a leading Indian table tennis player, renowned for her historic achievements. She became the first Indian woman to win an individual Commonwealth Games gold (2018) and reach the Olympic singles Round of 16 (Paris 2024). With three South Asian Games golds, two Commonwealth Games golds, and bronzes at the Asian Games, Asian Championships, and Asian Cup, she achieved a career-best world ranking of 27 (November 2024). Awarded the Major Dhyan Chand Khel Ratna (2020) and Arjuna Award (2018), Batra uses long pimple rubber to dominate opponents.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(223, 'GK', 'English', 'Achanta Sharath Kamal: From Chennai’s Courts to Commonwealth Games Glory', '11', '37', '119', 'd8530b827423999d36759145dfd239f6.jpg', '', '1758020400_Achanta Sharath Kamal_ From Chennai’s Courts to Commonwealth Games Glory.pdf', 'Achanta Sharath Kamal, born July 12, 1982, in Chennai, Tamil Nadu, is India’s most decorated table tennis player, with seven Commonwealth Games golds, two Asian Games bronzes, and two ITTF Pro Tour titles. A ten-time national champion, he competed in five Olympics (2004-2024), retiring in 2025 after a career-best world ranking of 30 (2019). Awarded the Padma Shri (2019) and Khel Ratna (2022), he transformed Indian table tennis.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(224, 'GK', 'English', 'K.T. Irfan: From Malappuram’s Fields to Olympic Race Walking Stardom', '11', '37', '119', 'aa2749beddb10a1ed5fceb727f739c97.jpg', '', '1758020827_K.T. Irfan_ From Malappuram’s Fields to Olympic Race Walking Stardom.pdf', 'K.T. Irfan, born February 8, 1990, in Malappuram, Kerala, is an Indian race walker and Indian Army Naib Subedar who set the national record in the 20km race walk (1:20:21) at the 2012 London Olympics, finishing 10th—India’s best Olympic race walking result. With a bronze at the 2017 Asian Championships and multiple national golds, he qualified for the Tokyo 2020 Olympics but finished 51st. At 35, he continues to compete, aiming for the 2025 National Games.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(225, 'GK', 'English', 'Arvind Singh: From Uttar Pradesh’s Farms to Olympic Rowing Stardom', '11', '37', '119', 'ac60904fa4f8e307801a21cdbb7402a6.jpg', '', '1758022031_Arvind Singh_ From Uttar Pradesh’s Farms to Olympic Rowing Stardom.pdf', 'Arvind Singh, born June 17, 1996, in Khabra, Uttar Pradesh, is an Indian rower and Indian Army Naib Subedar who won silver in the men’s lightweight double sculls at the 2019 and 2023 Asian Championships with Arjun Lal Jat. They achieved India’s best Olympic rowing finish (11th, Tokyo 2020). At 29, Singh continues training for future international events, including the 2025 Asian Championships.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(226, 'GK', 'English', 'Saurabh Chaudhary: From Village Talent to World Record-Holding Shooter', '11', '37', '119', '58101873ca3bcb74d53ad6210d9fb894.jpg', '', '1758023437_Saurabh Chaudhary_ From Village Talent to World Record-Holding Shooter.pdf', 'Saurabh Chaudhary, born May 12, 2002, in Kalina, Uttar Pradesh, is an Indian shooter specializing in the 10m air pistol, winning gold at the 2018 Asian Games at age 16, setting a Games record (240.7). With 19 international medals, including eight World Cup golds and a Youth Olympics gold (2018), he holds a world junior record (245.0, 2019). At 23, he’s reclaiming form after a Tokyo Olympics setback.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(227, 'GK', 'English', 'Manu Bhaker: From Haryana’s Small Town to Double Olympic Bronze Medalist', '11', '37', '119', '5ac63bc061fb4fb14870adc7438bcc19.jpg', '', '1758024692_Manu Bhaker_ From Haryana’s Small Town to Double Olympic Bronze Medalist.pdf', 'Manu Bhaker, born February 18, 2002, in Jhajjar, Haryana, is India’s most successful female shooter, winning two bronze medals at the Paris 2024 Olympics (10m air pistol, 10m air pistol mixed team), becoming the first Indian woman shooter to medal at the Olympics. With 22 World Championship and World Cup medals, including golds at the 2018 Commonwealth Games and 2018 Youth Olympics, she’s a trailblazer at 23.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(228, 'GK', 'English', 'Rajyavardhan Singh Rathore: From Olympic Silver to Rajasthan’s Cabinet Minister', '11', '37', '119', '2433c33685a7508590ecdbbf351903f1.jpg', '', '1758024982_Rajyavardhan Singh Rathore_ From Olympic Silver to Rajasthan’s Cabinet Minister.pdf', 'Colonel Rajyavardhan Singh Rathore, born January 29, 1970, in Jaisalmer, India, is an Olympic silver medalist in double trap shooting (Athens 2004), India’s first individual Olympic shooting medal. With 25 international medals, he joined the BJP in 2013, serving as Rajasthan’s Minister of Industry, Commerce, Youth Affairs, and Sports since 2023. Awarded the Padma Shri, he continues to shape Indian sports and politics.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(231, 'GK', 'English', 'Sushila Devi Likmabam: Manipur’s Judo Star and Olympic Trailblazer', '11', '37', '119', '8cc31fd3423ce0c8cff5b9431d75860e.jpg', '', '1758099181_Sushila Devi Likmabam_ Manipur’s Judo Star and Olympic Trailblazer.pdf', 'Sushila Devi Likmabam, born February 1, 1995, in Heingang, Manipur, India, is India’s most decorated judoka, competing in the women’s 48kg category. She won silver medals at the 2014 and 2022 Commonwealth Games, a gold at the 2019 South Asian Games, and represented India at the Tokyo 2020 Olympics, the first Indian judoka to do so. A Manipur Police officer since 2017, she overcame a career-threatening injury and depression to achieve global success. As of 2025, at age 30, she continues to compete and inspire, training for future international events.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(232, 'GK', 'Hindi', ' सुशीला देवी लाइकमबाम: मणिपुर की जूडो स्टार और ओलंपिक पथप्रदर्शक ', '11', '37', '119', '8f352ee62fd6151e4bdf2729332d7831.jpg', '', '1758100863__सुशीला देवी लाइकमबाम_ मणिपुर की जूडो स्टार और ओलंपिक पथप्रदर्शक (231).pdf', ' सुशीला देवी लाइकमबाम, जिनका जन्म 1 फरवरी 1995 को हेंगांग, मणिपुर, भारत में हुआ था, भारत की सबसे सफल जूडोका हैं, जो महिलाओं की 48 किग्रा श्रेणी में प्रतिस्पर्धा करती हैं। उन्होंने 2014 और 2022 राष्ट्रमंडल खेलों में रजत पदक, 2019 दक्षिण एशियाई खेलों में स्वर्ण पदक जीता और टोक्यो 2020 ओलंपिक में भारत का प्रतिनिधित्व किया, ऐसा करने वाली पहली भारतीय जूडोका बनीं। 2017 से मणिपुर पुलिस की अधिकारी, उन्होंने करियर-खत्म करने वाली चोट और अवसाद को पार करते हुए वैश्विक सफलता हासिल की। 2025 तक, 30 वर्ष की उम्र में, वह प्रतिस्पर्धा जारी रखे हुए हैं और प्रेरणा बनी हुई हैं, भविष्य की अंतरराष्ट्रीय प्रतियोगिताओं के लिए प्रशिक्षण कर रही हैं।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(233, 'GK', 'English', 'C.K. Nayudu: India’s First Test Captain and Cricketing Pioneer', '11', '37', '119', '2657e909a9a8ff0645763dbc92452797.jpg', '', '1758102379_C.K. Nayudu_ India’s First Test Captain and Cricketing Pioneer.pdf', 'Cottari Kanakaiya Nayudu, popularly known as C.K. Nayudu, was the first captain of the Indian cricket team in its debut Test match in 1932 against England. Renowned for his powerful batting and leadership, he laid the foundation for Indian cricket. A Padma Bhushan awardee, Nayudu is remembered as a trailblazer in Indian sports history.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(234, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'सी.के. नायडू: भारत के पहले टेस्ट कप्तान और क्रिकेटिंग अग्रदूत', '11', '37', '119', 'aecebe51fcbe6a2b344d2487db1321d4.jpg', '', '1758102725_सी.के. नायडू_ भारत के पहले टेस्ट कप्तान और क्रिकेटिंग अग्रदूत (233).pdf', 'कोट्टारी कनकैय्या नायडू, जिन्हें सी.के. नायडू के नाम से जाना जाता है, 1932 में इंग्लैंड के खिलाफ भारत की पहली टेस्ट टीम के कप्तान थे। अपनी विस्फोटक बल्लेबाज़ी और नेतृत्व के लिए प्रसिद्ध, उन्होंने भारतीय क्रिकेट की नींव रखी। पद्म भूषण से सम्मानित, नायडू भारतीय खेल इतिहास में एक पथप्रदर्शक के रूप में याद किए जाते हैं।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(235, 'GK', 'English', 'Lala Amarnath: India’s First Test Centurion and Iconic Captain', '11', '37', '119', 'dac4114b62f3298f7d99384e84ab12bb.jpg', '', '1758102920_Lala Amarnath_ India’s First Test Centurion and Iconic Captain.pdf', 'Lala Amarnath was the first Indian to score a Test century and later became India’s first cricket captain after independence. Renowned for his skill, leadership, and cricketing vision, he played a key role in shaping Indian cricket. He also served as a national selector and coach. Amarnath remains one of the most respected pioneers in Indian sports history.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(236, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'लाला अमरनाथ: भारत के पहले टेस्ट शतकवीर और प्रतिष्ठित कप्तान', '11', '37', '119', '9075a9fa8a728bee1484f3fe08cdf5bd.jpg', '', '1758103345_लाला अमरनाथ_ भारत के पहले टेस्ट शतकवीर और प्रतिष्ठित कप्तान (235).pdf', 'लाला अमरनाथ भारत के पहले क्रिकेटर थे जिन्होंने टेस्ट शतक लगाया और बाद में स्वतंत्र भारत के पहले कप्तान बने। अपने कौशल, नेतृत्व और क्रिकेट दृष्टिकोण के लिए प्रसिद्ध, उन्होंने भारतीय क्रिकेट को आकार देने में अहम भूमिका निभाई। उन्होंने राष्ट्रीय चयनकर्ता और कोच के रूप में भी कार्य किया। अमरनाथ भारतीय खेल इतिहास के सबसे सम्मानित अग्रदूतों में गिने जाते हैं।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(237, 'GK', 'English', 'Aditi Ashok: Pioneering Indian Women’s Golf on the Global Stage', '11', '37', '119', '64c4320090c7db6250ef4ba28060dabd.jpg', '', '1758103668_Aditi Ashok_ Pioneering Indian Women’s Golf on the Global Stage.pdf', 'Aditi Ashok, born March 29, 1998, in Bengaluru, India, is India’s leading female golfer, competing on the Ladies European Tour (LET) and LPGA Tour. She made history as the first Indian woman to play at the Olympics (Rio 2016), finishing fourth at Tokyo 2020, and competed at Paris 2024. With five LET titles, including the 2023 Andalucía Costa del Sol Open de España, and a 2023 Asian Games silver medal, Ashok has elevated golf’s profile in India. Known for her precision and putting, she continues to inspire at age 27.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(238, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'अदिति अशोक: वैश्विक मंच पर भारतीय महिला गोल्फ की अग्रदूत', '11', '37', '119', 'c6f5fb0c049f08415895f3b7ae76d6d9.jpg', '', '1758103873_अदिति अशोक_ वैश्विक मंच पर भारतीय महिला गोल्फ की अग्रदूत(237).pdf', 'अदिति अशोक, जन्म 29 मार्च 1998, बेंगलुरु, भारत, भारत की अग्रणी महिला गोल्फ़र हैं, जो लेडीज़ यूरोपियन टूर (LET) और एलपीजीए टूर पर खेलती हैं। वह ओलंपिक में खेलने वाली पहली भारतीय महिला (रियो 2016) बनीं, टोक्यो 2020 में चौथे स्थान पर रहीं और पेरिस 2024 में भी उतरीं। पाँच LET खिताबों और 2023 एशियाई खेलों के रजत पदक के साथ, उन्होंने भारत में गोल्फ की पहचान बढ़ाई। सटीकता और पुटिंग के लिए प्रसिद्ध, 27 वर्ष की उम्र में वह अभी भी प्रेरणा देती हैं।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(239, 'GK', 'English', 'Sunil Chhetri: India’s Record-Breaking Football Legend', '11', '37', '119', 'd50c944f2334f95b44e022f2d3b049b0.jpg', '', '1758104589_Sunil Chhetri_ India’s Record-Breaking Football Legend.pdf', 'Sunil Chhetri, born August 3, 1984, in Secunderabad, India, is India’s most celebrated footballer, captaining Bengaluru FC and the national team. With 97 goals in 155 international matches, he ranks fourth among all-time international goalscorers. Starting his career with Mohun Bagan in 2002, he played abroad with Kansas City Wizards and Sporting CP’s B team. Chhetri won multiple Nehru Cups, SAFF Championships, and the 2008 AFC Challenge Cup. Awarded the Arjuna (2011), Padma Shri (2019), and Khel Ratna (2021), he briefly retired in 2024 but returned in 2025.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(240, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'सुनील छेत्री: भारत के रिकॉर्ड-ब्रेकिंग फुटबॉल लीजेंड', '11', '37', '119', 'aa5d49e3dd45804a15655db0d2c423ed.jpg', '', '1758104789__सुनील छेत्री_ भारत के रिकॉर्ड-ब्रेकिंग फुटबॉल लीजेंड (239).pdf', ' सुनील छेत्री, 3 अगस्त 1984 को सिकंदराबाद, भारत में जन्मे, भारत के सबसे चर्चित फुटबॉलर हैं, जो बेंगलुरु एफसी और राष्ट्रीय टीम की कप्तानी करते हैं। 155 अंतरराष्ट्रीय मैचों में 97 गोलों के साथ, वे सर्वकालिक अंतरराष्ट्रीय गोलस्कोररों में चौथे स्थान पर हैं। मोहुन बागान से 2002 में करियर शुरू किया और विदेशों में भी खेले। उन्हें अर्जुन पुरस्कार (2011), पद्म श्री (2019) और खेल रत्न (2021) से सम्मानित किया गया।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(241, 'GK', 'English', 'Bhavani Devi: India’s First Olympic Fencer Breaks Barriers', '11', '37', '119', 'b82aeaa3ee6f98a059babdaccf98d971.jpg', '', '1758105121_Bhavani Devi_ India’s First Olympic Fencer Breaks Barriers.pdf', 'Chadalavada Anandha Sundhararaman Bhavani Devi, born August 27, 1993, in Chennai, India, is the first Indian fencer to compete at the Olympics (Tokyo 2020). Starting fencing at age 11, she overcame financial hardships, training with bamboo sticks due to equipment costs. She won gold at the 2017 World Cup satellite tournament and a historic bronze at the 2023 Asian Championships. Despite missing Paris 2024, she continues to inspire Indian fencing.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(242, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'भावनी देवी: भारत की पहली ओलिंपिक तलवारबाज', '11', '37', '119', 'ac42b78edf2ab0fb84dd3f9cc54c6b21.jpg', '', '1758105602_भावनी देवी_ भारत की पहली ओलिंपिक तलवारबाज (241).pdf', 'चदालवाडा आनंदा सुंदरारामन भावनी देवी, जन्म 27 अगस्त 1993, चेन्नई, भारत, भारत की पहली ओलिंपिक तलवारबाज हैं (टोक्यो 2020)। उन्होंने 11 वर्ष की उम्र में तलवारबाजी शुरू की और वित्तीय कठिनाइयों को पार किया। 2017 में वर्ल्ड कप सैटेलाइट में स्वर्ण और 2023 में एशियाई चैम्पियनशिप में कांस्य पदक जीतकर इतिहास रचा।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(243, 'GK', 'English', 'Fouaad Mirza: From Bangalore to Olympic Equestrian Glory', '11', '37', '119', '8143250a5d3984d979cd1630a0d74774.jpg', '', '1758105806_Fouaad Mirza_ From Bangalore to Olympic Equestrian Glory.pdf', 'Fouaad Mirza, born in Bangalore, India, on March 6, 1992, is a pioneering Indian equestrian. Growing up in a family with a rich equestrian heritage, he began riding at age five. Mirza won silver medals in individual and team eventing at the 2018 Asian Games, the first Indian to do so since 1982. He qualified for the 2020 Tokyo Olympics, marking a historic achievement. Training in Germany under Sandra Auffarth, he continues to inspire Indian equestrian sports.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(244, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'फुआद मिर्ज़ा: बैंगलोर से ओलंपिक अश्वारोही महिमा तक', '11', '37', '119', 'dc9fabb1a18fe2467529c2b6cd0b6920.jpg', '', '1758105976_फुआद मिर्ज़ा_ बैंगलोर से ओलंपिक अश्वारोही महिमा तक (243).pdf', 'फुआद मिर्ज़ा, 6 मार्च 1992 को बैंगलोर, भारत में जन्मे, एक अग्रणी भारतीय अश्वारोही हैं। समृद्ध अश्वारोही विरासत वाले परिवार में पले-बढ़े, उन्होंने पाँच वर्ष की उम्र में घुड़सवारी शुरू की। 2018 एशियाई खेलों में व्यक्तिगत और टीम इवेंटिंग में रजत पदक जीते—1982 के बाद ऐसा करने वाले पहले भारतीय। 2020 टोक्यो ओलंपिक के लिए क्वालीफाई कर उन्होंने ऐतिहासिक उपलब्धि हासिल की। जर्मनी में सैंड्रा औफार्थ के तहत प्रशिक्षण लेते हुए वे भारतीय अश्वारोही खेलों को प्रेरित कर रहे हैं।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(245, 'GK', 'English', 'Vijender Singh: India’s First Olympic Boxing Medalist and National Beacon', '11', '37', '119', '6e1e8b6fad615c7a32b69b04a124d71b.jpg', '', '1758106953_Vijender Singh_ India’s First Olympic Boxing Medalist and National Beacon.pdf', 'Vijender Singh made history by winning India’s first Olympic boxing medal—a bronze in middleweight at Beijing 2008. Soon crowned world #1, he claimed medals at the World Championships, Commonwealth Games, and Asian Games. He received the Khel Ratna (2009) and Padma Shri (2010). Later shifting to professional boxing and politics, he remains a symbol of discipline, resilience, and transformation in Indian sport. ', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(246, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'विजेंदर सिंह: भारत के पहले ओलंपिक बॉक्सिंग पदक विजेता और राष्ट्रीय प्रतीक', '11', '37', '119', 'd2c1a031de5c3af9ac0f3a51a00ef8dc.jpg', '', '1758107145_विजेंदर सिंह_ भारत के पहले ओलंपिक बॉक्सिंग पदक विजेता और राष्ट्रीय प्रतीक (245).pdf', 'विजेंदर सिंह ने बीजिंग 2008 में मिडिलवेट में कांस्य जीतकर भारत का पहला ओलंपिक बॉक्सिंग पदक जीता। विश्व नंबर 1 बनने के बाद उन्होंने विश्व चैंपियनशिप, राष्ट्रमंडल खेल और एशियाई खेलों में पदक जीते। 2009 में खेल रत्न और 2010 में पद्म श्री से सम्मानित। पेशेवर बॉक्सिंग और राजनीति में सक्रिय, वे भारतीय खेल में अनुशासन, दृढ़ता और प्रेरणा का प्रतीक बने।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(247, 'GK', 'English', 'Limba Ram: Tribal Boy from Rajasthan Who Nearly Clinched Olympic Glory', '11', '37', '119', '3b593d4a0a729c55f57fdd97eea13069.jpg', '', '1758107466_Limba Ram_ Tribal Boy from Rajasthan Who Nearly Clinched Olympic Glory.pdf', 'Limba Ram, from a humble Ahari tribal background in Rajasthan, rose to global archery prominence in the late 1980s and early ’90s. He equalled a world-record at the 1992 Asian Championships and narrowly missed an Olympic bronze at Barcelona. A three-time Olympian and former national champion, he later coached India before being honoured with the Arjuna Award (1991) and Padma Shri (2012).', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(248, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'लिंबा राम: राजस्थान का आदिवासी लड़का, जिसने ओलंपिक में करीब सफलता पाई', '11', '37', '119', '570d9202e01dbc5e8847fbdba89f4931.jpg', '', '1758107695_लिंबा राम_ राजस्थान का आदिवासी लड़का, जिसने ओलंपिक में करीब सफलता पाई (247).pdf', 'लिंबा राम, राजस्थान के एक मामूली आहरी आदिवासी परिवार से, 1980-90 के दशक में विश्व आर्चरी में प्रमुख बने। 1992 एशियाई चैम्पियनशिप में उन्होंने विश्व रिकॉर्ड बराबर किया और बार्सिलोना ओलंपिक में कांस्य से चूक गए। तीन बार के ओलंपियन और पूर्व राष्ट्रीय चैंपियन, उन्होंने बाद में भारत के लिए कोचिंग की और अर्जुन पुरस्कार (1991) तथा पद्म श्री (2012) से सम्मानित हुए।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(249, 'GK', 'English', 'Deepika Kumari: India’s Archer Par Excellence, World No. 1 Pioneer', '11', '37', '119', 'd291ca8c00089633c09939b38049617d.jpg', '', '1758108524_Deepika Kumari_ India’s Archer Par Excellence, World No. 1 Pioneer.pdf', 'Deepika Kumari is India’s trailblazing recurve archer—first from her country to rise to World No. 1 in 2012. A four-time Olympian, she has earned medals at the World Championships, Commonwealth, Asian Games, and a rich haul in Archery World Cups. Known for her precision and resilience, she won the Arjuna Award (2012) and Padma Shri (2016) for her exceptional sporting contributions', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(250, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'दीपिका कुमारी: भारत की शिखर तीरंदाज, विश्व नंबर 1 प्रवर्तक', '11', '37', '119', 'c1fcf29dc3d05d1cc526dbb97d42affc.jpg', '', '1758108703_दीपिका कुमारी_ भारत की शिखर तीरंदाज, विश्व नंबर 1 प्रवर्तक (249).pdf', 'दीपिका कुमारी भारत की अग्रणी रिकर्व तीरंदाज हैं—पहली भारतीय जिन्होंने 2012 में विश्व नंबर 1 का स्थान प्राप्त किया। चार बार की ओलंपियन, उन्होंने विश्व चैम्पियनशिप, राष्ट्रमंडल, एशियाई खेल और आर्चरी वर्ल्ड कप में कई पदक जीते। अपनी सटीकता और दृढ़ता के लिए जानी जाती हैं। 2012 में अर्जुन पुरस्कार और 2016 में पद्म श्री से सम्मानित।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(251, 'GK', 'English', 'Geet Sethi: Billiards Legend, Nine-Time World Champion', '11', '37', '119', '91bbe6420fc2479e5905bb1b0cc05f09.jpg', '', '1758184761_Geet Sethi_ Billiards Legend, Nine-Time World Champion.pdf', 'Geet Sethi, born April 17, 1961, in Delhi, is India’s iconic billiards player, dominating the sport in the 1990s. With nine world titles (five professional, three amateur), he holds a record 1276-point break in 1992. A Padma Shri and Rajiv Gandhi Khel Ratna recipient, Sethi co-founded Olympic Gold Quest and runs Raag Travels, inspiring Indian sports.', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(252, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'गीत सेठी: बिलियर्ड्स के दिग्गज, नौ बार विश्व चैंपियन', '11', '37', '119', 'c502e371665a5e9443d4f6a824123788.jpg', '', '1758184961_गीत सेठी_ बिलियर्ड्स के दिग्गज, नौ बार विश्व चैंपियन (251).pdf', 'गीत सेठी, 17 अप्रैल 1961 को दिल्ली में जन्मे, 1990 के दशक में भारत के प्रतिष्ठित बिलियर्ड्स खिलाड़ी रहे। उन्होंने नौ विश्व खिताब जीते (पाँच प्रोफेशनल, तीन अमेच्योर) और 1992 में 1276-पॉइंट ब्रेक का रिकॉर्ड बनाया। पद्म श्री और राजीव गांधी खेल रत्न प्राप्त, उन्होंने ओलंपिक गोल्ड क्वेस्ट की सह-स्थापना की और राग ट्रैवल्स संचालित कर भारतीय खेलों को प्रेरित किया।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(253, 'GK', 'English', 'Dhyan Chand: Hockey’s Wizard, Three-Time Olympic Champion', '11', '37', '119', '3481ab21e8cebb69d5f18b72827b8759.jpg', '', '1758185752_Dhyan Chand_ Hockey’s Wizard, Three-Time Olympic Champion.pdf', 'Dhyan Chand (1905–1979), born in Allahabad, India, was a legendary field hockey player, leading India to Olympic golds in 1928, 1932, and 1936. Nicknamed “The Wizard,” he scored over 400 international goals, dominating global hockey. A Major in the Indian Army, his legacy endures through the Dhyan Chand National Stadium, inspiring Indian sports. He died in 1979 from liver cancer.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(254, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'ध्यानचंद: हॉकी के जादूगर, तीन बार के ओलंपिक चैम्पियन', '11', '37', '119', '8badf0ae72bef7a5e2942c60d72bfe8e.jpg', '', '1758185968_ध्यानचंद_ हॉकी के जादूगर, तीन बार के ओलंपिक चैम्पियन (253).pdf', 'ध्यानचंद (1905–1979), इलाहाबाद, भारत में जन्मे, एक दिग्गज फील्ड हॉकी खिलाड़ी थे जिन्होंने भारत को 1928, 1932 और 1936 ओलंपिक में स्वर्ण पदक दिलाए। “द विज़ार्ड” के नाम से मशहूर, उन्होंने 400 से अधिक अंतरराष्ट्रीय गोल दागे और विश्व हॉकी पर दबदबा बनाया। भारतीय सेना में मेजर रहे, उनकी विरासत ध्यानचंद राष्ट्रीय स्टेडियम और नेशनल स्पोर्ट्स डे से आज भी जीवित है। 1979 में उनका निधन लीवर कैंसर से हुआ।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(255, 'GK', 'English', 'P.T. Usha: India’s Sprint Queen, Olympic Trailblazer', '11', '37', '119', '5878238fb4383d14747d7852685a6d59.jpg', '', '1758186632_P.T. Usha_ India’s Sprint Queen, Olympic Trailblazer.pdf', 'P.T. Usha, born June 27, 1964, in Payyoli, Kerala, is India’s legendary track and field athlete, nicknamed the “Payyoli Express.” She won four Asian Games golds and nearly medaled at the 1984 Los Angeles Olympics, finishing fourth in the 400m hurdles. A Padma Shri recipient, she coaches young athletes and serves as Indian Olympic Association president, inspiring generations.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(256, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'पी.टी. उषा: भारत की स्प्रिंट क्वीन, ओलंपिक पथप्रदर्शक', '11', '37', '119', 'ac4e15ad897e0d8a66d8ed6117ecb82b.jpg', '', '1758187103_पी.टी. उषा_ भारत की स्प्रिंट क्वीन, ओलंपिक पथप्रदर्शक (255).pdf', 'पी.टी. उषा, 27 जून 1964 को पय्योली, केरल में जन्मीं, भारत की महान धाविका हैं जिन्हें “पय्योली एक्सप्रेस” कहा जाता है। उन्होंने एशियाई खेलों में चार स्वर्ण पदक जीते और 1984 लॉस एंजेलिस ओलंपिक में 400 मीटर हर्डल्स में चौथा स्थान प्राप्त किया। पद्मश्री से सम्मानित, वे युवा खिलाड़ियों को प्रशिक्षित करती हैं और भारतीय ओलंपिक संघ की अध्यक्ष के रूप में कार्यरत हैं।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(257, 'GK', 'English', 'Milkha Singh: Flying Sikh, India’s Iconic Track Legend', '11', '37', '119', '826efb68738ad5ceebbd5d1330275c1a.jpg', '', '1758187547_Milkha Singh_ Flying Sikh, India’s Iconic Track Legend.pdf', 'Milkha Singh (1929–2021), born in Layalpur, Punjab (now Pakistan), was India’s first Commonwealth Games gold medalist (1958, 440 yards). Known as the “Flying Sikh,” he won four Asian Games golds and nearly medaled at the 1960 Rome Olympics (fourth, 400m). His inspiring journey from partition refugee to athletics icon, overcoming personal tragedies, left a lasting legacy in Indian sports.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(258, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'मिल्खा सिंह: फ़्लाइंग सिख, भारत के प्रतिष्ठित ट्रैक लीजेंड', '11', '37', '119', '055ea43c711a5b9093b133ee6a9d7db2.jpg', '', '1758187915_मिल्खा सिंह_ फ़्लाइंग सिख, भारत के प्रतिष्ठित ट्रैक लीजेंड (256).pdf', 'मिल्खा सिंह (1929–2021), जिनका जन्म लायलपुर, पंजाब (अब पाकिस्तान) में हुआ था, भारत के पहले कॉमनवेल्थ खेलों के स्वर्ण पदक विजेता थे (1958, 440 यार्ड्स)। “फ़्लाइंग सिख” के नाम से मशहूर, उन्होंने चार एशियाई खेलों में स्वर्ण जीते और 1960 रोम ओलंपिक में (400 मीटर, चौथा स्थान) लगभग पदक जीत लिया। विभाजन के शरणार्थी से लेकर एथलेटिक्स के प्रतीक बनने तक की उनकी प्रेरणादायक यात्रा, निजी त्रासदियों पर विजय पाकर, भारतीय खेलों में अमिट छाप छोड़ गई।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(259, 'GK', 'English', 'Ravi Kumar Dahiya: Olympic Silver Medalist and Wrestling Prodigy', '11', '37', '119', '8bab5bbc2e745439c2ed47aa0028a9e6.jpg', '', '1758188392_Ravi Kumar Dahiya_ Olympic Silver Medalist and Wrestling Prodigy.pdf', 'Ravi Kumar Dahiya, born December 12, 1997, in Nahri, Haryana, is an Indian freestyle wrestler who won a silver medal at the 2020 Tokyo Olympics. A three-time Asian champion and 2019 World Championships bronze medalist, he trains at Chhatrasal Stadium. Despite injuries, he secured gold at the 2022 Commonwealth Games. Currently, he aims for gold at the 2028 LA Olympics.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(260, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'रवि कुमार दहिया: ओलंपिक रजत पदक विजेता और कुश्ती के धुरंधर', '11', '37', '119', '3aec51dba5c00918b7865ef22cdebcd3.jpg', '', '1758188829_रवि कुमार दहिया_ ओलंपिक रजत पदक विजेता और कुश्ती के धुरंधर (259).pdf', 'रवि कुमार दहिया, 12 दिसंबर 1997 को नहरी, हरियाणा में जन्मे, भारत के फ्रीस्टाइल पहलवान हैं जिन्होंने टोक्यो ओलंपिक 2020 में रजत पदक जीता। वे तीन बार एशियाई चैंपियन और 2019 विश्व कुश्ती चैम्पियनशिप के कांस्य पदक विजेता रहे हैं। वे छत्रसाल स्टेडियम में प्रशिक्षण लेते हैं। चोटों के बावजूद, उन्होंने 2022 राष्ट्रमंडल खेलों में स्वर्ण पदक जीता। वर्तमान में उनका लक्ष्य लॉस एंजेलिस ओलंपिक 2028 में स्वर्ण जीतना है।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(261, 'GK', 'English', 'Vinesh Phogat: Olympic Finalist, Congress MLA, New Mother', '11', '37', '119', '2a347c51bd76a2a2511fe4e0de0570ce.jpg', '', '1758189150_Vinesh Phogat_ Olympic Finalist, Congress MLA, New Mother.pdf', 'Vinesh Phogat, born August 25, 1994, in Charkhi Dadri, Haryana, is a retired Indian freestyle wrestler and Congress MLA from Julana. The first Indian woman to reach an Olympic wrestling final (Paris 2024), she won gold at the 2018 Asian Games and three Commonwealth Games. After her Olympic disqualification, she entered politics and welcomed a son in 2025.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(262, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'विनेश फोगाट: ओलंपिक फाइनलिस्ट, कांग्रेस विधायक', '11', '37', '119', 'aa8095ec0fa9a044c02ae827ac68eb8f.jpg', '', '1758189472_विनेश फोगाट_ ओलंपिक फाइनलिस्ट, कांग्रेस विधायक (261).pdf', 'विनेश फोगाट, 25 अगस्त 1994 को चरखी दादरी, हरियाणा में जन्मीं, एक सेवानिवृत्त भारतीय फ्रीस्टाइल पहलवान और जुलाना से कांग्रेस विधायक हैं। वे पेरिस ओलंपिक 2024 में फाइनल में पहुँचने वाली पहली भारतीय महिला पहलवान बनीं। उन्होंने 2018 एशियाई खेलों और तीन राष्ट्रमंडल खेलों में स्वर्ण पदक जीते। पेरिस ओलंपिक में डिसक्वालिफिकेशन के बाद उन्होंने राजनीति में प्रवेश किया और 2025 में बेटे को जन्म दिया।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(263, 'GK', 'English', 'Yogeshwar Dutt: Olympic Bronze Medalist and Wrestling Legend', '11', '37', '119', 'f4dfba8fb2b644100fb6fea77d3d7419.jpg', '', '1758189750_Yogeshwar Dutt_ Olympic Bronze Medalist and Wrestling Legend.pdf', 'Yogeshwar Dutt, born November 2, 1982, in Bhainswal Kalan, Haryana, is a retired Indian freestyle wrestler. He won a bronze medal at the 2012 London Olympics and golds at the 2010 and 2014 Commonwealth Games and 2014 Asian Games. A Padma Shri recipient, he mentors wrestlers and joined BJP politics in 2019, advocating for sports development.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(264, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'योगेश्वर दत्त: ओलंपिक कांस्य पदक विजेता और कुश्ती के दिग्गज', '11', '37', '119', 'f6f16dbea9e389c4cbd8b021a63c6a64.jpg', '', '1758190535_योगेश्वर दत्त_ ओलंपिक कांस्य पदक विजेता और कुश्ती के दिग्गज (263).pdf', 'योगेश्वर दत्त, जिनका जन्म 2 नवम्बर 1982 को भैंसवाल कलां, हरियाणा में हुआ, एक पूर्व भारतीय फ्रीस्टाइल पहलवान हैं। उन्होंने 2012 लंदन ओलंपिक में कांस्य पदक जीता और 2010 व 2014 कॉमनवेल्थ खेलों तथा 2014 एशियाई खेलों में स्वर्ण पदक हासिल किया। पद्मश्री से सम्मानित योगेश्वर 2019 में बीजेपी से राजनीति में जुड़े और खेलों के विकास की वकालत कर रहे हैं।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(265, 'GK', 'English', 'Lakshya Sen: Olympic Semifinalist and Badminton’s Bright Future', '11', '37', '119', '93cd09b63c34da6b47fe74b65590eec7.jpg', '', '1758190594_Lakshya Sen_ Olympic Semifinalist and Badminton’s Bright Future.pdf', 'Lakshya Sen, born October 16, 2001, in Almora, Uttarakhand, is a rising Indian badminton player. Trained at the Prakash Padukone Badminton Academy, he won bronze at the 2021 BWF World Championships and reached the semifinals at the Paris 2024 Olympics. With titles like the 2022 Commonwealth Games gold, Sen’s aggressive style and resilience have made him a global contender.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(266, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'लक्ष्य सेन: ओलंपिक सेमीफ़ाइनलिस्ट और बैडमिंटन का उज्ज्वल भविष्य', '11', '37', '119', '92ef562865c6701d2bf40fad4fb787d9.jpg', '', '1758191305_लक्ष्य सेन_ ओलंपिक सेमीफ़ाइनलिस्ट और बैडमिंटन का उज्ज्वल भविष्य (265).pdf', 'लक्ष्य सेन, जन्म 16 अक्टूबर 2001, अल्मोड़ा, उत्तराखंड, भारत, एक उभरते हुए भारतीय बैडमिंटन खिलाड़ी हैं। प्रकाश पादुकोण बैडमिंटन अकादमी में प्रशिक्षित, उन्होंने 2021 बीडब्ल्यूएफ विश्व चैम्पियनशिप में कांस्य और पेरिस 2024 ओलंपिक में सेमीफ़ाइनल तक का सफ़र तय किया। 2022 कॉमनवेल्थ गेम्स स्वर्ण विजेता लक्ष्य अपने आक्रामक खेल और जुझारूपन के कारण वैश्विक स्तर पर मज़बूत दावेदार बन चुके हैं।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(267, 'GK', 'English', 'Kidambi Srikanth: From World No. 1 to Thomas Cup Hero', '11', '37', '119', 'e0768553b2e4b0652db8605b7eaba92b.jpg', '', '1758191518_Kidambi Srikanth_ From World No. 1 to Thomas Cup Hero.pdf', 'Kidambi Srikanth, born February 7, 1993, in Ravulapalem, Andhra Pradesh, is a pioneering Indian badminton player. The first Indian male to reach World No. 1 in 2018, he won a silver medal at the 2021 BWF World Championships and led India to its historic 2022 Thomas Cup victory. Trained at the Gopichand Academy, Srikanth’s aggressive style and notable titles, including the 2014 China Open, have inspired a generation.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(268, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'किदांबी श्रीकांत: विश्व नंबर 1 से थॉमस कप हीरो तक', '11', '37', '119', 'd7dbd2058be64c07ce2b4d3cc5a15e7e.jpg', '', '1758192142_किदांबी श्रीकांत_ विश्व नंबर 1 से थॉमस कप हीरो तक (267) .pdf', 'किदांबी श्रीकांत, जन्म 7 फ़रवरी 1993, रावुलापालेम, आंध्र प्रदेश, एक अग्रणी भारतीय बैडमिंटन खिलाड़ी हैं। 2018 में विश्व नंबर 1 बनने वाले पहले भारतीय पुरुष खिलाड़ी, उन्होंने 2021 बीडब्ल्यूएफ विश्व चैंपियनशिप में रजत पदक जीता और 2022 में भारत को ऐतिहासिक थॉमस कप विजय दिलाई। गोपीचंद अकादमी में प्रशिक्षित श्रीकांत की आक्रामक शैली और 2014 चाइना ओपन जैसे उल्लेखनीय खिताबों ने एक पीढ़ी को प्रेरित किया है।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(269, 'GK', 'English', 'Mahesh Bhupathi: India’s Doubles Legend and Grand Slam Pioneer', '11', '37', '119', '18fd4d4364506e049f63469a2826df64.jpg', '', '1758192681_Mahesh Bhupathi_ India’s Doubles Legend and Grand Slam Pioneer.pdf', 'Mahesh Bhupathi, born June 7, 1974, in Chennai, India, is a retired tennis player renowned for being the first Indian to win a Grand Slam in 1997. With 12 Grand Slam titles (four men’s doubles, eight mixed doubles), he achieved a career mixed doubles Grand Slam. Bhupathi founded the International Premier Tennis League, served as India’s Davis Cup captain, and established Globosport and ZEVEN.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(270, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'महेश भूपति: भारत के डबल्स लीजेंड और ग्रैंड स्लैम पायनियर', '11', '37', '119', 'fbb141251a44b93846db085ef0623173.jpg', '', '1758193954_महेश भूपति_ भारत के डबल्स लीजेंड और ग्रैंड स्लैम पायनियर (269).pdf', 'महेश भूपति, जन्म 7 जून 1974, चेन्नई, भारत, एक सेवानिवृत्त टेनिस खिलाड़ी हैं जो 1997 में ग्रैंड स्लैम जीतने वाले पहले भारतीय बने। 12 ग्रैंड स्लैम खिताबों (चार पुरुष युगल, आठ मिश्रित युगल) के साथ उन्होंने करियर मिक्स्ड डबल्स ग्रैंड स्लैम पूरा किया। भूपति ने इंटरनेशनल प्रीमियर टेनिस लीग की स्थापना की, भारत के डेविस कप कप्तान रहे, और ग्लोबोसपोर्ट तथा ZEVEN की नींव रखी।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(271, 'GK', 'English', 'Somdev Devvarman: NCAA Champion, Asian Games Hero and Indian Trailblazer', '11', '37', '119', '1f2360a13f436dc5cdb1269a501c3305.jpg', '', '1758194154_Somdev Devvarman_ NCAA Champion, Asian Games Hero and Indian Trailblazer.pdf', 'Somdev Devvarman, India’s pioneering men’s singles tennis star, won consecutive NCAA singles titles in 2007–08 with a historic 44–1 record. He was the first Indian to reach ATP finals in Chennai (2009) and South Africa (2011). He clinched Commonwealth gold in 2010 and both singles and doubles gold at the 2010 Asian Games. Post-retirement, he mentors Indian tennis development', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(272, 'GK', 'Hindi', ' सोमदेव देववर्मन: एनसीएए चैंपियन, एशियाई खेलों के हीरो और भारतीय पथप्रदर्शक', '11', '37', '119', '72d1eaacd3ebce192db6eeff898d684d.jpg', '', '1758194401__सोमदेव देववर्मन_ एनसीएए चैंपियन, एशियाई खेलों के हीरो और भारतीय पथप्रदर्शक (271).pdf', 'सोमदेव देववर्मन, भारत के अग्रणी पुरुष एकल टेनिस खिलाड़ी, ने लगातार दो एनसीएए खिताब (2007–08) जीते और 2008 में 44–1 का ऐतिहासिक रिकॉर्ड बनाया। उन्होंने चेन्नई (2009) और दक्षिण अफ्रीका (2011) में एटीपी फाइनल खेले तथा विश्व रैंकिंग में 62वें स्थान तक पहुँचे। राष्ट्रमंडल और एशियाई खेलों (2010) में स्वर्ण जीतने के बाद 2017 में संन्यास लिया। संन्यास के बाद वे युवा भारतीय खिलाड़ियों को मार्गदर्शन देते हैं।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(273, 'GK', 'English', 'Rohan Bopanna: India’s Tennis Dynamo, Oldest Doubles World No.1', '11', '37', '119', '996b4f6ef03ef737f6cdaf8429985daa.jpg', '', '1758195258_Rohan Bopanna_ India’s Tennis Dynamo, Oldest Doubles World No.1.pdf', 'Rohan Bopanna, born 4 March 1980 in Bangalore, became world No. 1 in men’s doubles at 43 after winning the 2024 Australian Open with Matthew Ebden. A Grand Slam champion and Masters 1000 winner, he has collected 26 ATP doubles titles. A Padma Shri awardee and inspiration for athletes over 40, he continues mentoring through his tennis academy.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(274, 'GK', 'Hindi', ' रोहन बोपन्ना: भारत के टेनिस डायनमो, सबसे उम्रदराज़ डबल्स वर्ल्ड नं. 1', '11', '37', '119', '177f317af4f3eebcf1498b953c80d7c7.jpg', '', '1758195450__रोहन बोपन्ना_ भारत के टेनिस डायनमो, सबसे उम्रदराज़ डबल्स वर्ल्ड नं. 1 (273).pdf', 'रोहन बोपन्ना, जिनका जन्म 4 मार्च 1980 को बेंगलुरु में हुआ, ने 43 वर्ष की आयु में मैथ्यू एब्डेन के साथ 2024 ऑस्ट्रेलियन ओपन जीतकर पुरुष युगल विश्व नं. 1 का स्थान हासिल किया। वे ग्रैंड स्लैम और मास्टर्स 1000 चैंपियन हैं और 26 एटीपी युगल खिताब जीत चुके हैं। पद्मश्री से सम्मानित बोपन्ना, 40 वर्ष से ऊपर के एथलीटों के लिए प्रेरणा और अपनी अकादमी के ज़रिए मार्गदर्शक हैं।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(275, 'GK', 'English', 'Rani Rampal: From Small‑Town Girl to India’s Hockey Trailblazer', '11', '37', '119', '40e57b48e82b1508c02456f3f3169833.jpg', '', '1758196314_Rani Rampal_ From Small‑Town Girl to India’s Hockey Trailblazer.pdf', 'Rani Rampal, India’s celebrated women’s hockey forward and former captain, debuted internationally at age 15 in 2008. She scored 205 goals in 254 appearances and led India to its best-ever Olympic finish (4th place at Tokyo 2020). The recipient of Padma Shri and Khel Ratna, she retired in 2024 and now coaches India’s U‑18 women’s team.', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(276, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'रानी रामपाल: छोटे-कस्बे की लड़की से भारत की हॉकी पथप्रदर्शक', '11', '37', '119', 'bf24135ac1682f955680c5610615666c.jpg', '', '1758196659_रानी रामपाल_ छोटे-कस्बे की लड़की से भारत की हॉकी पथप्रदर्शक (275).pdf', 'रानी रामपाल, भारत की मशहूर महिला हॉकी फॉरवर्ड और पूर्व कप्तान, ने 2008 में 15 वर्ष की उम्र में अंतरराष्ट्रीय पदार्पण किया। उन्होंने 254 मैचों में 205 गोल किए और भारत को उसके अब तक के सर्वश्रेष्ठ ओलंपिक परिणाम (टोक्यो 2020 में चौथा स्थान) तक पहुँचाया। पद्मश्री और खेल रत्न से सम्मानित रानी ने 2024 में संन्यास लिया और अब भारत की अंडर-18 महिला टीम को प्रशिक्षित कर रही हैं।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(277, 'GK', 'English', 'Abhinav Bindra: India’s First Individual Olympic Gold Medalist and Visionary', '11', '37', '119', 'b7123a272be71c69b974e6142e4c8422.jpg', '', '1758197552_Abhinav Bindra_ India’s First Individual Olympic Gold Medalist and Visionary.pdf', 'Abhinav Bindra, India’s first-ever individual Olympic gold medalist, clinched the 10 m air rifle title at Beijing in 2008. A former world champion (2006 Zagreb), he dominated international shooting through meticulous preparation and elite technique. Post-retirement in 2016, Bindra founded performance‑tech ventures, chaired sports science initiatives, and received the Olympic Order in 2024 for his enduring impact.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(278, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'अभिनव बिंद्रा: भारत के पहले ओलंपिक स्वर्ण पदक विजेता और दूरदर्शी', '11', '37', '119', 'dcc9a9bf6851e6fa9cbd79eeceb252e5.jpg', '', '1758197753_अभिनव बिंद्रा_ भारत के पहले ओलंपिक स्वर्ण पदक विजेता और दूरदर्शी (277).pdf', 'अभिनव बिंद्रा, भारत के पहले व्यक्तिगत ओलंपिक स्वर्ण पदक विजेता, ने 2008 बीजिंग खेलों में 10 मीटर एयर राइफल खिताब जीता। 2006 ज़ाग्रेब विश्व चैंपियनशिप विजेता रहे बिंद्रा ने सूक्ष्म तैयारी और उच्च तकनीक से अंतरराष्ट्रीय शूटिंग पर दबदबा बनाया। 2016 में संन्यास के बाद उन्होंने प्रदर्शन-तकनीक उपक्रम स्थापित किए और 2024 में ओलंपिक ऑर्डर से सम्मानित हुए।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(282, 'GK', 'English', 'Viswanathan Anand: India’s Chess Pioneer, Five‑Time World Champion Maestro', '11', '37', '119', 'f3b8c1731f14ff191335acf3b10cedb0.jpg', '', '1758271353_Viswanathan Anand_ India’s Chess Pioneer, Five‑Time World Champion Maestro.pdf', 'Viswanathan Anand, India’s first grandmaster (1988), became a five‑time world chess champion — in 2000, 2007, 2008, 2010, and 2012. Renowned for his rapid play and versatility across formats, he revived chess in India. As of 2022, he serves as Deputy President of FIDE. An inspirational mentor, he continues to nurture emerging talents through his academy and national outreach programs.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(283, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'विश्‍वनाथन आनंद: भारत के शतरंज के पथप्रदर्शक, पांच बार के विश्व चैम्पियन मास्ट्रो', '11', '37', '119', '99fd89a2353baebcf8e908fbab1f1340.jpg', '', '1758271600_विश्_वनाथन आनंद_ भारत के शतरंज के पथप्रदर्शक, पांच बार के विश्व चैम्पियन मास्ट्रो (282).pdf', 'विश्‍वनाथन आनंद, भारत के पहले ग्रैंडमास्टर (1988), पांच बार विश्व शतरंज चैम्पियन बने — 2000, 2007, 2008, 2010 और 2012 में। तेज खेल और विभिन्न प्रारूपों में उनकी बहुमुखी प्रतिभा के लिए प्रसिद्ध, उन्होंने भारत में शतरंज को पुनर्जीवित किया। 2022 तक वे FIDE के उपाध्यक्ष हैं। एक प्रेरक मेंटर के रूप में, वे अपनी अकादमी और राष्ट्रीय कार्यक्रमों के माध्यम से युवा प्रतिभाओं को प्रशिक्षण देते हैं।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(284, 'GK', 'English', 'P.V. Sindhu: Olympic Medalist, World Champion, and Indian Legend', '11', '37', '119', 'b7e4cb8261c0010515ec6d2b54bad599.jpg', '', '1758272225_P.V. Sindhu_ Olympic Medalist, World Champion, and Indian Legend.pdf', 'Pusarla Venkata Sindhu burst onto the world stage with an Olympic silver in 2016, becoming the first Indian woman to win multiple Olympic medals when she secured bronze in Tokyo 2020. A world championship gold medalist and first Indian to win five singles medals at the event, she remains a key figure in Indian sports and a role model for aspiring athletes', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(285, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'पी. वी. सिंधु: ओलंपिक पदक विजेता, विश्व चैंपियन और भारतीय दिग्गज', '11', '37', '119', 'e773f153f8d267a65603ddc0b3edb338.jpg', '', '1758272406_पी. वी. सिंधु_ ओलंपिक पदक विजेता, विश्व चैंपियन और भारतीय दिग्गज (284).pdf', 'पुसर्ला वेंकट सिंधु ने 2016 ओलंपिक रजत जीतकर विश्व मंच पर धमाकेदार प्रवेश किया और टोक्यो 2020 में कांस्य जीतकर कई ओलंपिक पदक जीतने वाली पहली भारतीय महिला बनीं। विश्व चैम्पियनशिप की स्वर्ण पदक विजेता और उस टूर्नामेंट में पांच एकल पदक जीतने वाली पहली भारतीय, सिंधु भारतीय खेलों की एक प्रमुख शख्सियत और नए खिलाड़ियों की आदर्श बनी हुई हैं।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(286, 'GK', 'English', 'Bajrang Punia: India’s Olympic Wrestling Medalist and Padma Awardee', '11', '37', '119', '13a3857fcbad6d2829fb2eb487fad9b9.jpg', '', '1758273165_Bajrang Punia_ India’s Olympic Wrestling Medalist and Padma Awardee.pdf', 'Bajrang Punia is a decorated Indian freestyle wrestler known for his aggressive techniques and consistent performance. He won a bronze medal in the 2020 Tokyo Olympics (held in 2021) in the 65 kg category and is a multiple-time World Championship medalist. A recipient of the Padma Shri and Khel Ratna, Punia is among India’s finest modern wrestlers.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(287, 'GK', 'Hindi', 'बजरंग पुनिया: भारत के ओलंपिक पहलवान और पद्म सम्मानित', '11', '37', '119', '0be1beb20d35d45ec0b8d538136f0fff.jpg', '', '1758273591_बजरंग पुनिया_ भारत के ओलंपिक पहलवान और पद्म सम्मानित (286).pdf', 'बजरंग पुनिया एक सम्मानित भारतीय फ्रीस्टाइल पहलवान हैं, जो अपनी आक्रामक तकनीकों और लगातार प्रदर्शन के लिए प्रसिद्ध हैं। उन्होंने 2020 टोक्यो ओलंपिक (2021 में आयोजित) में 65 किग्रा वर्ग में कांस्य पदक जीता और कई बार विश्व चैम्पियनशिप में पदक हासिल किया। पद्मश्री और खेल रत्न से सम्मानित, बजरंग भारत के आधुनिक युग के श्रेष्ठ पहलवानों में गिने जाते हैं।\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
